SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first first Moderna shot on 12/30/21. At first I had the common cold like symptoms, like fatigue that are associated with the vaccine. That month I started to have little heart flutters, but after I looked up heart flutters on internet, and it said that they aren't serious, I didn't worry about it. I also had an incident that month when I was driving where my left arm got completely numb. After I received the second shot on 2/3/21, I took 3 days off from work, because I wasn't feeling well. I had flu like symptoms, with no fever, but went back to work, because the symptoms felt mild enough. I had some additional pressure in my ears that came and went. I was still having bad cases of fatigue and light headedness. On February 12, I woke up with extreme fatigue. I felt so dizzy that it felt like my head was at the bottom of a swimming pool. I had to get fingerprinted for work so I drove with symptoms. When I went in to get fingerprinted, I fainted and was rushed to the hospital. My EKG came back normal while I was laying down so I was released that day. My symptoms were worse with intense PVCs, fatigue, neusea, lightheadedness, dizziness, migraines, vision problems and GI issues. I followed up with my PCP and after testing she suspected that I had POTS syndrome. After having to leave my jobs because the symptoms were so bad and I moved back to State for better medical care, I followed up with more doctors and was diagnosed with POTs Syndrome. After phsyical therapy, acupuncture, and lifestyle changes, my symptoms have gotten better but I still have them. Lately, I have had a  lot of PVCs. I have severely lost income, because I couldn't work.
LAB_DATA: Blood tests, Heart monitoring while laying sitting and standing, 30 day heart monitor, heart echocardiogram, pulmonary artery sonogram, MRI, EEG, Ambulatory EEG, tilt-table test

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Later that evening after the vaccine I got so tired I just couldn't stay awake resulting in me laying down a little earlier than usual. About a week and a half later several times I would get a feeling like I was coming down with a cold with a burning sensation in the chest, a sore throat, severe coughing and sneezing was associated and occurred periodically throughout the day. This occurred off and on for about three weeks, finally about a week and a half ago the cold symptoms diminished. Since the vaccine I have this feeling in my chest as if I have pressure baring down on my sternum area which is still occurring to date causing me to not wear a bra because it feels as if it is on too tightly. When I laid down it felt as if I could feel my heart doing a flip but this also occurred only at rest, when laying down and upon the exhale of breath feeling as if it was skipping a beat and I could feel it in my throat area. No pain is associated but it wakes me up at night sometimes because of the discomfort and it scares the heck out of me. I was given a solution to try to alleviate the pressure on my sternum but it didn't work. I was monitored for a while and released from the hospital ER. I have an appointment tomorrow with my PCP for further evaluation.

Pt was vaccinated with Johnson and Johnson vaccine in May 2021.  Pt's son passed away from COVID-19 infection. The patient tested positive on 10/5/2021.  The patient was transferred to bigger hospital from smaller Hospital with COVID-19 pneumonia and sepsis. When the patient arrived to bigger hospital the patient had a pulseless electrical activity cardiac arrest requiring chest compressions and 1 dose of epinephrine prior to returning to spontaneous circulation. The patients post cardiac echocardiogram showed an ejection fraction decreased to 23%, the pt. also developed acute kidney injury related to acute tubular necrosis.  The patient was given tocilizumab, remdesivir and steroids.  The patient's hospital course was further complicated by DVT and pulmonary embolism.  Pt was noted to also have right upper lobe necrotizing pneumonia due to Pseudomonas.  Pt was seen and was on Meropenem.  Pt was unable to be weaned off of the ventilator and underwent a tracheostomy on 10/27/2021 and a PEG placement on 10/29/2021.  The patient's family met with palliative care and they wanted to continue current care.  On admission to Select the patient was on assit-control mode of ventilation with a tidal volume of 380, PEEP of 5, respiratory rate of 14 and FiO2 of 40%.  The pt. had also had pneumothoraxes and on admission to Select the pt. had 2 right sided chest tubes and a chest tube on the left.  Pt's condition worsened and on 11/12/2021 Pulmonary noted that he had a long discussion with the family, discussed with them the surgical additional chest tube placement needed, but family decided on comfort cares at  that time.  Pt was placed on comfort cares and expired on 11/12/2021 at 1500.

He had a CT and CTA of the brain at hospital that showed no acute process and an LP was attempted but unsuccessful. The patient was then transferred to Larger hospital and was see by neurology, who obtained MRI of the L spine and EMG, LP was preformed and showed no infectious cause. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hospitalized 11/12/2021; COVID-19 positive 11/12/2021; fully vaccinated  BRIEF OVERVIEW: Admission Date: 11/12/2021 Discharge Date: 11/15/2021 DETAILS OF HOSPITAL STAY: HOSPITAL COURSE: Patient is a 81 y.o. female who presented to the Hospital with shortness of breath due to COVID-19. Also reported dry cough, nasal congestion, fatigue, diarrhea and chest pain radiating to her back.  At the ER she was tested positive for COVID-19. ECG showed first degree AV block, cardiac monitoring was put on. She was hypoxic when presenting to the ER at 89% room air, and was put on a 2L nasal cannula.  She was weaned off a oxygen requirement during the hospital course. Troponin levels were negative. CRP were trending downwards and d-dimer remained elevated in the 1,000's. She was given remdesivir and decadron in the ER and continued in admission. CTA thorax found massive distension of the cervical and thoracic esophagus.  On 11/14 early morning the patient became increasingly combative and agitated. She did not know her name and attempted to kick and yell at the staff. She attempted to remove her IV and put it in her mouth. She was given Haldol and she attempted to remove IV access again. Decadron was stopped later that morning and was only continued with remdesivir.  Patients daughter was able to calm the patient down and was calm during the rest of the hospital course.  On discharge day, the patient was orient to person place and time and was calm, non combative. She was sitting comfortably on room air. Remdesivir was discontinued and she was taken home by her daughter. PT and OT assessed her and recommended to be discharge to home with PT and OT home assist. RT evaluated the patient and reported that the patient does not need to be discharged with oxygen requirement

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Per H&P: 25 y.o. female  with PMHx of AIHA requiring recent hospitalization and asthma who presents with symptomatic anemia and Hb of 4.8 on outpatient labs from 11/8.    Patient had a recent hospitalization at hospital in October 2021.  She had been experiencing increased lightheadedness, fatigue, weakness, and headaches and was found to have a hemoglobin of 6.6.  As she is a denomination  she deferred any blood transfusions.  Work-up demonstrated positive Coombs, CD3, parvovirus IgG, decreased haptoglobin (<8), erythropoietin 77, and elevated reticulocyte site count.  Hematology was consulted and started methylprednisolone, IVIG, EPO x2.  IR BM biopsy showed normocellular marrow with trilineage hematopoiesis, elevated reticulin fibrosis, no elevated blasts.  She was discharged on a prednisone 60 taper which she has completed and scheduled outpatient hematology follow-up.  Patient reports that she only experienced minimal improvement with treatment during that hospitalization.     She notes that following that hospitalization, she continued to experience weakness and numbness in her legs, tremors in her extremities when exerting herself for long periods, and dyspnea on exertion.  She states that she feels intermittently fatigued but was noticeably more fatigued yesterday.  She continues to have occasional headaches which is relieved with migraine medication.  Also notes intermittent loss of appetite. Reports that she feels better overall than compared to her last admission. Denies any chest pain, lightheadedness, or shortness of breath currently.  Denies any signs of bleeding.  Patient has been taking iron supplements and completed her steroid taper on 11/7.  Last menstrual period was earlier this month and she notes that flow was more inconsistent but does not feel like menstruation was heavier than normal.  Reports that her twin sister also has hx of anemia which has required hospitalization in the past but is unaware of any other family history of hematological conditions. She is currently on leave of absence from work due to her medical issues until next week.
LAB_DATA: 11/12/21 1022 11/11/21 2207 11/11/21 0404 11/10/21 1237 WBC 1.5*  --  1.5* 1.7* HEMOGLOBIN 4.8*  --  4.7* 4.6* HEMATOCRIT 15.5*  --  15.3* 15.3* PLATELETS 255  --  298 292 PROTIME  --  13.8  --  14.1 INR  --  1.0  --  1.1 PTT  --  50*  --  42*       11/11/21 2207 C3 COMPLEMENT 95 C4 COMPLEMENT 18   Lab Results Component Value Date   % Iron Saturation 31 11/10/2021   Ferritin 10.9 11/10/2021   Lab Results Component Value Date   C3 Complement 95 11/11/2021   C4 Complement 18 11/11/2021  Per Rheumatology:  #Autoimmune hemolytic anemia Current hemoglobin 4.7 Positive ANA with a titer of>1:2560 in speckled pattern, positive Coombs test, low haptoglobin level, mildly elevated LDH Complement level normal at outside hospital, further serologies for lupus or APS were not sent Bone marrow biopsy at Hospital with normocellular marrow with trilineage hematopoiesis, no increased blast Patient is s/p pulse dose of steroids and IVIG followed by prednisone taper started with 60 mg daily and completed on 11/7  Patient does not have any symptoms related to CTD like skin rash, joint pain, oral ulcers, alopecia, serositis or history of blood clots or pregnancy losses however  should work-up further as hemolytic anemia can be associated with some autoimmune disease like lupus or antiphospholipid,  Syndrome.  High titer positive ANA is concerning.    -Check dsDNA, anti-Smith, anti-RNP, SSA, SSB -Repeat complement levels, C3, C4 -Check APS labs with lupus anticoagulant, beta-2 glycoprotein, anticardiolipin -Check UA with urine microscopy, urine protein and creatinine ratio -Would recommend starting  high-dose steroids 1mg /kg daily, would  round to 80 mg daily and taper 10 mg down every week -Ensure GI prophylaxis with PPI while on steroids -Ensure PCP prophylaxis with Bactrim DS Monday Wednesday Friday -Check TPMT antibody -We will screen for hepatitis B, C and tuberculosis -Continue IV iron infusion -Continue folic acid supplement   Per Hematology: #Coombs positive autoimmune hemolytic anemia -Patient is a status post methylprednisolone, IVIG and steroid taper completed on 11/7. -Was also noted to have high ANA titer at Hospital was >1:2560 speckled, for that I would recommend considering rheumatology consultation to rule out an underlying autoimmune process -Although her reticulocyte count is high, its not consistent with her very low hemoglobin which points towards a combination of hypoproliferative anemia (iron deficiency) and hemolytic anemia. Between 2014 at 2015 she was to follow-up with Doctor for iron deficiency anemia and had a positive Coombs test and presence of panagglutinin was presumed to be the result of her prior transfusion as a child.  At that time had LDH, bilirubin, haptoglobin and reticulocyte count were normal. -Repeat Coombs test positive, but negative with eluate -Due to her believes, no blood transfusion - continue IV iron replacement (125mg daily x 5 days) and p.o. folic acid  -For Blood conservation ->use pediatric phlebotomy tubes. Minimize unnecessary lab draws  -I have reviewed her peripheral smear which shows features of polychromasia, macrocytosis with no peripheral blasts -I will request her pathology slides from Hospital for a second review patient signed consents to release HIT information. -Mixing study: Normal PT and prolonged PTT with complete correction consistent with weak lupus inhibitor or mild factor VIII, 9 or 11 deficiency. Factor 8 high, follow-up factor 9 and 11 (sent 11/12/21). - Can consider EPO if worsens - continue prednisone 80mg daily for now, Hgb slightly improved

HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS: Patient is a 82 y.o. male who presents today with fatigue and increased cough, congestion shortness of breath.  Patient also reports significant diarrhea in which he is most concerned.  Patient has a history of CVA, hypertension, coronary artery disease, CKD, and diabetes.  Patient reported 6 days of not taking his home medication and restarted today. Due to his continued feeling of fatigue and diarrhea, patient presented to ED for further care.  In the emergency department, patient was found to be hypoxic requiring 6 L nasal cannula to maintain oxygen saturation greater than 90%.  Patient was also found to have increased creatinine greater than his baseline CKD, with hypoglycemia.  Patient was given IV dextrose with resolved.  Patient also had chest x-ray which showed COVID pneumonia and CHF essentially unchanged from previous exam 2 days prior.  Patient was given 1 dose remdesivir and transferred to hospitalist service for continued care. Assessment/Plan    ASSESSMENT / PLAN:   * Acute respiratory disease due to COVID-19 virus Assessment & Plan Patient reports onset diarrhea on 11/10/2021, with continued fatigue and shortness of breath. Also, c/o fever, decreased appetite and oral intake.  Patient reports he has not taken his home medications in 5-6 days.    Patient remained on 100% high flow nasal cannula throughout the night with p.r.n. non-rebreather supplemental oxygen. She was found to be COVID-19 positive despite being vaccinated. In the ER, she was found to have hyponatremia (126) and hypoxia. She was given fluids and started on Decadron + Remdesivir. Patient required 3 L o2 via NC to maintain saturations. It was later felt that bronchospasm from COPD-E was contributing to her symptoms. Decadron was transitioned to IV Solumedrol, nebs were given and Spiriva was added to her home bronchodilators.  Throughout her stay, she was clinically stable but was unable to be completely weaned from oxygen.  By the day of discharge, Patient was eager to go home. She will need 2 L of oxygen at the time of discharge. She has transitioned to PO Prednisone and will continue a taper. Glucose levels were well controlled on insulin during admission. She may transition back to her home oral anti-hyperglycemic regimen at discharge. BP was intermittently elevated- recommend follow up with pcp to determine if anti-hypertensive medications are needed. Discharge instructions were printed and explained. All questions were answered.  Please note that Patient had mild hyperkalemia that was improved on labs today.  Probiotic/Fiber sent to help with diarrhea.

Provider ordered Pfizer Biontech 30 mcg/0.3 ml Covid 19 vaccine for patient 17 year old male. Nurse LPN prepared vaccine (She had inquired earlier for clarification on dilution for the Pfizer as she doesn't mix it typically, She was advised 1.8 ml for regular Pfizer. Inadvertently mixed a Peds dose Pfizer vial formulated for 5-11 year olds. It was discovered before parent left as staff notice a vial of the Ped dose was open and she knew we were not yet using that vaccine. The only Peds doctor working at that time was Dr so she checked with provider to see if he had indeed ordered a Ped dose for someone. He said he did not, then stated he just ordered a regular Pfizer for a client. We then check with the nurse and inquired what vaccine vial was used to give the Pfizer she just had gave and where which container did she give it from. It was indeed the Ped dose. Dr. spoke with patient and parent. It was then decided that an additional dose of the Ped Pfizer vaccine would be given @ 0.2 ml It was discussed to check for possible additional information and deemed by provider to proceed ( A new separate vial was open and mixed as it was unknown at that particular time to which degree the previous vial was diluted) The additional dose was administered at 0.2 ml as requested by provider. The information for the additional dose was documented in the original order with explanation of what was given. Provider had stated there wasn't a separate order available at that time. Patient was held for an additional 15 minutes had no issues or complaints and released with parent. When the Pfizer Ped dosage was received the previous week, the vaccine coordinator, staff placed it in the Main fridge on a separate shelf from the regular Pfizer. It was kept in its original box and placed in a plastic bag marked as Ped Pfizer 5-11 years and was then tagged with a sticker as a visual method to make it stand out as different. It was also placed in a Blue bin marked with a sticker. The blue bin was also marked as Pfizer Ped 5-11 only, dosage 0.2 ml and the Diluent amount all written on bin. Regular Pfizer has always been kept in a green bin on the middle shelf of the unit. After intendent the Blue bin was removed from Main fridge and was relocated to the other fridge with a Note on it stating do not use. I also added two additional stickers 1 High Alert and 1 Look alike Sound alike stickers were placed on both Pfizer vaccine bins although now in different units I thought it maybe helpful being as proactive additional prevention till asses by those who investigate such matters as to what best method for storage should be. It was reported to nursing supervisor as well.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I suddenly had aphasia while discussing dinner with my husband.  I couldn't recognize the name of the food he suggested.  More accurately, I recognized the word, but I couldn't recognize the connection between the word and the actual food that I knew we both meant -- and I couldn't find the right word.  The Aphasia lasted about 15 minutes.  It affected only my ability to recognize nouns, and only those nouns related to our dinner discussion.  We went to the ER out of concern that I might be having a stroke. I was admitted, but examination and an MRI showed no signs of stroke or other abnormality. I was released 24 hours later.  For about a week afterwards, I could tell that my brain was retrieving some nouns a nanosecond more slowly than normal when I was speaking, although it was not something anyone talking with me could have perceived.  After a week or so, that resolved and there have been no symptoms since.  Several months later, an article about a surgeon suffering from Long Covid quoted him as describing an almost identical experience. He offered it as an example of the "brain fog" he had experienced since contracting Covid.
Vaccine administered beyond the Best Used Date but before expiration date.

I normally only do 28 units of long-acting insulin at night and very rarely need correction doses with short-acting. I did not do a correction dose and kept an eye on it. My levels came back down and I went to bed around 10 pm feeling a little achy.  I woke up the next morning(11/14/21) with achy joints,  hot sweats, a raging headache, and nausea. I stayed in bed all morning finally eating a piece of whole-grain bread to take ibuprofen around noon. At that point, my fasting blood sugar was over 150. The piece of bread sent me over 250. I ate very little the remaining of the day because I felt awful and my blood sugar remained over 150. 11/15/21 Monday. Still feeling sick with achy joints, hot sweats, headaches, and nausea. Call in sick from work. Fasting sugars are still well over 100. Any time I eat anything my blood sugar shoots well over 200. I corrected in the afternoon with 4 units of novolog (which I haven't had to do in a very long time) and it tanked my blood sugar only for it to spike back up to over 200 when I ate something. Could not maintain his sats so intubated. Tested positive for Covid with imaging consistent with Covid pneumonia. I believe he was vaccinated. CRP 13.4 on admission, will repeat in a.m. Has been extubated a few days now with improving oxygenation -Supplemental oxygen -Finished remdesivir -10 days of dexamethasone done on 11/17  -On baricitinib   Hypothyroidism Assessment & Plan TSH on 11/16 was 35.6. Patient hesitant to start thyroid replacement as he says he did not have any symptoms before covid infection -Recheck TSH as an outpatient.    A-fib  Assessment & Plan Noted to have a few runs of afib in ICU. Completed amiodarone infusion a couple days ago. Monitor on tele for recurrence. Did not discuss AC with him, has not had an echo. Will check a TSH. Resting HRs low 60s in SR so held off on nodal blockers.    Elevated LFTs Assessment & Plan Moderate transaminase elevation noted. Likely COVID related. Monitor CMP. Improved while here (ALT/AST of 151/70 on day of discharge), recommend rechecking as an outpatient. Approx. 3hrs after the vaccine shot, I started to get GBS symptoms starting with my feet becoming numb and a few hours later in the night, it progressed to my lower legs and by the next day on 8/21/21(12-24 hrs after the shot) I had also heavy leg weakness, increased numbness on lower body, right hip pain and dull numb feeling of my head. On 8/22/21, I had worsening GBS symptoms - stomach, chest, lower back, arms, hands, head, legs & feet numbness, more weakness, fatigue and nausea. All of the same symptoms I had with prior GBS experience. Over the next several weeks, the GBS symptoms have fluctuated increasing and decreasing in severity.  Also had occassional ankle popping sounds when walking & small short duration muscle tremors in my right upper thigh area.  On a few occasions I felt as though I need to go to the ER for GBS treatment but was able to get through the worse episodes.  Over time for the 3 months since I had the vaccine shot the GBS symptoms have gradually began to decrease in intensity.  Although some symptons are still present such as numb feet and head issues and occasional other body areas, the overall symptoms have lessened at this point after 3 months.  Based on my reaction to the 1st vaccine dose, I and my doctors agree that I should not get the 2nd dose.  I am sending this to you as the CDC website indicates that it is okay for persons with GBS to get the COVID-19 vaccine but no mention of these potential reactions. I checked the box for "Life threatening illness" as GBS is a serious condition that can quickly become life threatening should the symptoms accelerate quickly which could cause paralysis and death.  I did not feel that I was approaching that point but the possibility was still present due to the unpredictable nature of GBS.
LAB_DATA: No medical test performed other than medical examinations by doctor. I checked the box "Unknown" as I have substantially recovered but not fully recovered as of this date.

HISTORY: Guillian Barre' Syndrome (GBS).  Acquired Fall of 2020.  GBS symptoms began slowing with numbness in one foot then progressed to both feet and then progressed further up the body and had other symptoms such as foot drop in my right foot over the course of about 4-5 weeks while my primary care doctor - neurolgist, were doing medical tests on me to figure out what was causing these issues.  My condition worsened to the point I went back to the ER and was diagnosed with subacute GBS and treated with 5 doses of IVIG starting on 10/17/21.  Symptoms improved somewhat but my conditioned worsened again several weeks later and I had to return to the ER and recieved a 2nd IVIG treatment (5 doses) starting on12/10/21.  That was my last and final IVIG treatment.  Afterwards, my GBS symptoms had fluctuated in severity with occassion substaintial flare ups but in general have been on the decline.  The last major flare up was in late January 2021but since then on mild occurences and since April only slight  or very mild numbness could be generally noticed prior to the vaccine shot on 8/20/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within three hours extreme fatigue, fever of 101F, body aches, feeling of coming down with influenza like symptoms, and, in terms of feelings, PTSD from having had COVID-19 in December 2019 and from having the same adverse side effects after every vaccination. I am a stable, balanced individual but in addition to feeling sick, I was angry, sad, and spent an entire day crying. I know that my body was "recognizing" the m-RNA vector in the vaccine, but why was it fighting so hard against COVID-19 that it brought me back to my knees for a fourth time? If my immunity was built in by the infection and then two vaccines (given in March and April 2021 after a year of self-quarantine), why do I keep reacting with such severity? I called my doctor who advised me to report this...I am also part of the study being done by the regarding who may have had COVID-19 before it was a "thing." I may have "long COVID" because I've lost hair, my once cast-iron stomach has become 'rusted' since being so ill, and I am doing my level best to understand what is going on with this virus, this pandemic, and the vaccines. I do not mean to be whiny; I merely feel a call to act after suffering. Thank you for reading this--and I hope you've remained above this crisis.

He did require multiple continuous drips that included dopamine, Neo-Synephrine, Levophed, vasopressin, milrinone, heparin, amiodarone, Bumex, Precedex, and dopamine drips during the hospitalization. I administered the patient's 1st Moderna dose in our vaccination room.  The patient was not showing any signs of reaction. The patient then went to our observation area in front of the pharmacy. Five minutes after vaccination, he presented to the pharmacy window stating that he felt faint. A pharmacy technician immediately opened the pharmacy door and put a chair under the patient, as he passed out into it.  I instructed another technician to call 911. I ran to the patient who then stopped breathing.  I grabbed an Epi-pen off the pharmacy shelf and was about to administer it when the patient regained consciousness.  The patient was very pale, but oriented to person, place and time. EMS arrived, gathered information, and left with the patient.

Rash initially started as a single itchy blister distal to injection site on anterior forearm. Rash multiplied into a shingles like rash- made a doctor's appointment and received antiviral medication. After 1 day of medication rash crossed the midline and was told it could be a poison ivy. Steroid cream prescribed and no relief given after several days. Rash continued to spread and evolved into a target lesion rash on both forearms, upper arms, chest, abdomen, thighs, calves, ankles, feet, toes, plantar surface, palms of hands, fingers, neck and face. Returned to doctor and was given a 12 day taper of prednisone. No relief of itching or spreading after 7 days. Rash started healing slowly and after finishing steroid,  rash reappeared on right and left forearms, abdomen and thighs. Was referred to an allergist while on the steroid. Dr. did a blood test for lyme disease and shingles iGg. Lyme was negative, shingles iGg was positive, but not high enough to indicate recent outbreak. Rash started resolving after several days. One week after resolution, rash reappeared and Dr. performed a biopsy. Results of biopsy were hypersensitivity reaction. Rash is still reoccuring as of 11/18/2021.
LAB_DATA: Blood test for Lyme and Shingles iGg- 10/06/2021 Lyme- negative Shingles iGg- positive Biopsy of rash- 10/18/2021 diagnosis- hypersensitivity reaction

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Per Mothers report: Patient was vaccinated, then watched his brother get vaccinated and said "whoa", then walked to the waiting area and was looking at items when he got pale and slumped against his brother down to the floor.   He apparently lost consciousness momentarily or certainly lost clarity.   Mother called for help and patient was placed on a cot.  Mother called for help.   I found the patient to be diaphoretic, cool, and bradycardic with a weak pulse by palpation at the wrist.  There was no rash, redness, nor airway tightness.  Indications were that this was a case of syncope.   There was no witness of a head injury and no scalp tenderness.  Legs were elevated and patient drank sips of water.  After 20 minutes, with parents collaboration, patient was moved outdoors to "fresh air" where he sat on a chair several minutes and then walked slowly then rapidly, finally achieving better color and a strong pulse.   Patient went home with both parents - on e driving and one observing.   Call back at 4:50 pm (approx 2.5 hrs after vaccination) the patient was snacking and drinking and improving slowly.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt pretty lethargic in the weeks following after the second Pfizer dose and generally felt worse in the gym for several weeks, but I didn't really consider that it could have been the vaccine.  In July, I had palpitations, chest pain, and shortness of breath while at rest at work requiring labetalol and oxygen.  I was seen in an emergency room supposed to be admitted to hospital for cardiology for an echo and cardiac MRI, but I didn't have health insurance and was concerned about the bill.  I've been a paramedic for about six years to put the following statements in context- medical providers make the worst patients.  I didn't get any formal results from the hospital, but my 12-lead was a sinus rhythm with diffuse ST elevation with no reciprocal depression, heart rate around 140. I left the hospital AMA and took high dose aspirin (650mg 3 times per day) for two weeks.  I slept for about two days initially, and then had consistent lethargy to the point of getting out of breath washing the dishes or taking the trash out.  My symptoms were gone after 10 or 11 days and I stopped the aspirin a few days after that.  I have no cardiac history.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have spinal stenosis.today it feels just like it did before the treatments; the skin has a tint of green; My arm is swollen/My arm is huge; I couldn't move my arm an inch; I was sleeping a lot; my arm hurt so bad; fever of 99.5�F; chills; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of VACCINATION SITE MOVEMENT IMPAIRMENT (I couldn't move my arm an inch), HYPERSOMNIA (I was sleeping a lot), SPINAL STENOSIS (I have spinal stenosis.today it feels just like it did before the treatments), VACCINATION SITE DISCOLOURATION (the skin has a tint of green) and VACCINATION SITE PAIN (my arm hurt so bad) in a 79-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 032F21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     Concurrent medical conditions included Spinal stenosis. On 12-AUG-2021, the patient was vaccinated with first dose of hpv rl1 6 11 16 18 31 33 45 52 58 vlp vaccine (yeast)(GARDASIL 9), intramuscularly for prophylaxis (exact dose, dose number, lot #, expiration date and anatomical location of administration were not reported). On unspecified date, approximately in 2021, the patient wanted to commit suicide and on unknown, previous date, patient was admitted to hospital, was experiencing chest pain (electrocardiogram (EKG) looked fine) with patient's White Blood Cell (WBC) count being high. Patient was then transferred to a mental health facility to address patient's depression where he started 'seeing things, hearing things,' and wanted to commit suicide. On unknown, previous date in 2021, while at mental health facility, the patient was administered nadolol in response to patient's blood pressure being elevated. Patient was transferred to hospital emergency room where had experienced acute psychosis and was still having chest pains at which point computer tomography scan was performed. On unknown date in 2021, he was transferred to 'another mental health facility,' second, separate, mental health facility, where patient's acute psychosis was better; however, his labs were off with potassium being high, and the patient was transferred to hospital where was diagnosed with hypothyroidism, elevated liver enzymes, protein in patient's spinal fluid. He was stabilized at hospital, and was sent to third, separate, mental health facility; where the physician's advice was for patient to remain hospitalized. Upon internal review, the events of suicidal intention, acute psychosis, CSF protein abnormal and hypothyroidism were determined to be medically significant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: EYELIDS WERE INFLAMED; DIFFICULTY SLEEPING; FATIGUE; HEAD TINGLING; PERIPHERAL NEUROPATHY; ADVERSE EVENT; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 55 year old adult female. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's past medical history included: covid-19 in JUN-2020, and concurrent conditions included: non-smoker. The patient had no history of drug abuse or illicit drug use. The patient received Covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of administration not reported, batch number: 202A21A expiry: unknown) dose was not reported, 01 total administered on 29-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. No concomitant medications were reported.  The patient mentioned that, she had already contracted covid in JUN-2020, but took the shot for preventive purposes even though she had antibodies in December 2020. On 04-MAY-2021, the patient experienced adverse event. On 04-MAY-2021 patient had her wellness exam and she told the doctor that her head, feet and hands were tingling. She was told to give it 6-8 weeks to see if symptoms subside. The symptoms did not go away after 6 weeks and were getting worse. Her obstetrician-gynecologists (OBGYN) sent her to the primary care physician (PCP) and they did not give her much to help. In JUL-2021 patient went to a neurologist because her symptoms were getting progressively worse. Patient was going to a neurologist, acupuncturist and even an ophthalmologist because her eye lids were inflamed. She has had 3 magnetic resonance imaging tests (MRIs), a spinal tap, and among other tests with nothing was coming back positive. The patient was told that she is suffering from peripheral neuropathy. While she was getting better, it was still a struggle and it took an emotional and financial toll on her. The patient was treated with Gabapentin and Cymbalta. She had difficulty sleeping, and was fatigued.  The action taken with Covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient recovered from difficulty sleeping, and was recovering from adverse event, peripheral neuropathy, eyelids were inflamed, fatigue, and head tingling. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0 20211136843- COVID-19 VACCINE AD26.COV2.S-peripheral neuropathy. This event(s) is considered unassessable. The event(s) has a compatible/suggestive temporal relationship, is unlabeled, and has unknown scientific plausibility. There is no information on any other factors potentially associated with the event(s).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fever; chills; body aches; Vaccine exposure during pregnancy; This spontaneous retrospective pregnancy case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of PYREXIA (Fever), CHILLS (chills), MYALGIA (body aches) and EXPOSURE DURING PREGNANCY (Vaccine exposure during pregnancy) in a 34-year-old female patient (gravida 1, para 1) who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination.     The patient's past medical history included Ex-alcohol user (1-3 drinks/week prior to conceiving), Subfertility (treated with 2 cycles of Femara April and May 2020), Subacute thyroiditis and Hypothyroidism. Family history included Developmental hip dysplasia (maternal grandmother , maternal aunt and mother of patient). Concurrent medical conditions included Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, Postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (Postural orthostatic tachycardia), Polyneuropathy, Sleep apnea (complex sleep apnea), Fruit allergy (pomegranate), Fragrance sensitivity, Drug allergy (Teriparatide) and Allergy (seminal plasma). Concomitant products included DOXYLAMINE SUCCINATE, PYRIDOXINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BONJESTA) and ONDANSETRON for Nausea, LEVOTHYROXINE from an unknown date to 15-Jul-2021 for Subacute thyroiditis and Hypothyroidism, MINERALS NOS, VITAMINS NOS (PRENATAL VITAMINS [MINERALS NOS;VITAMINS NOS]), VITAMIN D3 and MAGNESIUM for an unknown indication.   On an unknown date, the patient received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. The patient's last menstrual period was on 21-May-2020 and the estimated date of delivery was 24-Feb-2021. On an unknown date, the patient experienced PYREXIA (Fever), CHILLS (chills), MYALGIA (body aches) and EXPOSURE DURING PREGNANCY (Vaccine exposure during pregnancy). The patient received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) during pregnancy. The vaginal delivery occurred on 12-Feb-2021, which was reported as Full-term. For neonate 1, The outcome was reported as Delivered NOS. Live, full-term birth. At the time of the report, PYREXIA (Fever), CHILLS (chills) and MYALGIA (body aches) outcome was unknown and EXPOSURE DURING PREGNANCY (Vaccine exposure during pregnancy) had resolved. Not Provided    DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 17-Jun-2020, Pregnancy test: positive (Positive) Positive pregnancy test. On 07-Aug-2020, Ultrasound uterus: normal (normal) normal. On 19-Nov-2020, Glucose tolerance test: normal (normal) normal. On an unknown date, Ultrasound uterus: normal (normal) normal ultrasounds at MFM OB every 1-2 weeks.         No treatment medication was provided.  After second dose patient had fever, chills, body aches and once had decreased fetal movement in the middle of the night after receiving second Moderna dose earlier that morning. Patient called the doctor and was instructed to go to ER where fetal ultrasound was normal, and was not admitted after several hours of monitoring.   Baby was induced 1 week later continued decreased fetal movement and patient also had neuropathy so it wasn't clear whether it was actually decreased fetal movement or whether could not detect it. Either way, there was a marked decrease in fetal movement towards the end of pregnancy.  This is a regulatory case concerning a 34-year-old  female patient with medical history of Subfertility (treated with 2 cycles of Femara April and May 2020), Subacute thyroiditis and Hypothyroidism,  who experienced vaccine exposure during pregnancy and the non serious expected events  of pyrexia and myalgia after receiving the second  dose of mRNA-1273 (time to onset is unknown). Patient received both doses during pregnancy. Information regarding the child case can be seen in  case MOD-2021-259303. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pneumonia in one of her lungs and possible blood clot; Pneumonia in one of her lungs/ Left lobe pneumonia; Coughing up blood; Feeling sick; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of PULMONARY THROMBOSIS (Pneumonia in one of her lungs and possible blood clot), PNEUMONIA (Pneumonia in one of her lungs/ Left lobe pneumonia) and HAEMOPTYSIS (Coughing up blood) in a 65-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.    Co-suspect product included non-company product TREPROSTINIL SODIUM (TYVASO) inhalation gas for Pulmonary arterial hypertension.    Concurrent medical conditions included Pulmonary arterial hypertension. Concomitant products included TADALAFIL for an unknown indication.   On 10-Sep-2020, the patient started TREPROSTINIL SODIUM (TYVASO) (unknown route) at an unspecified dose four times per day. On 01-Nov-2021, the patient received third dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 01-Nov-2021, the patient experienced PULMONARY THROMBOSIS (Pneumonia in one of her lungs and possible blood clot) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant), PNEUMONIA (Pneumonia in one of her lungs/ Left lobe pneumonia) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant), HAEMOPTYSIS (Coughing up blood) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and MALAISE (Feeling sick). The patient was hospitalized on 01-Nov-2021 due to HAEMOPTYSIS, PNEUMONIA and PULMONARY THROMBOSIS. At the time of the report, PULMONARY THROMBOSIS (Pneumonia in one of her lungs and possible blood clot), PNEUMONIA (Pneumonia in one of her lungs/ Left lobe pneumonia), HAEMOPTYSIS (Coughing up blood) and MALAISE (Feeling sick) outcome was unknown.            After 18 hours later at night of receiving Moderna COVID vaccine booster dose, patient started feeling sick, had chest pain, and started coughing up blood. The patient was rushed to the emergency department, where they (physician) found that patient had pneumonia in one of lungs and possible blood clot. The patient was diagnosed with left lobe pneumonia. The patient had been hospitalized on same date for hemoptysis and pneumonia.  On 02-Nov-2021, patient was scheduled for angiogram. The patient was still in the hospital (at the time of this report).  Treatment medications was not reported. Tyvaso  delivered by Inhalation Device, 18-54 microgram (3-9 breaths), four times a day.  Company comment: This case concerns a 65-year-old female patient with a relevant medical history of Pulmonary arterial hypertension undergoing treatment with tadalafil and Treprostinil, who experienced the unexpected serious (hospitalization and medically significant) event/AESI of Haemoptysis, Pneumonia and Pulmonary thrombosis after mRNA- 1273 Moderna vaccine. The onset of the event occurred approximately 18 hours after the booster dose of mRNA- 1273 vaccine. Clinical manifestations included chest pain, malaise and haemoptysis. Final diagnosis of left lobe pneumonia and provisional diagnosis of pulmonary thrombosis were done. The rechallenge is not applicable since the event occurred after the booster dose. Underlying pulmonary hypertension and concomitant treatment with tadalafil and treprostinil remain a confounder/confounder. intracranial hypertension; small vessel ischemic changes; vasculitis; the booster dose on 17Sep2021; body aches; headache/ migraine; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer reported for herself. A 40-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (COMIRNATY), dose 3 via an unspecified route of administration on 17Sep2021 (Lot Number: FC3183) as DOSE 3 (BOOSTER), SINGLE for COVID-19 immunisation at the age of 40 years old. Medical history included ongoing addison's disease. Concomitant medication(s) included pneumococcal vaccine (PNEUMOCOCCAL VACCINE) taken for immunisation on 13Sep2021; hydrocortisone (HYDROCORTISONE) taken for addison's disease; fludrocortisone (FLUDROCORTISONE) taken for addison's disease.  The patient previously received first dose of BNT162B2 on 18Dec2020 (Lot Number: EJ1685, Expiry: Mar2021) and received 2nd dose of BNT162B2 on 07Jan2021 (Lot Number: EL3248, Expiry: Apr2021) for COVID-19 immunisation both at the age of 39 years old, and both experienced body aches, headache, chills, low grade fever.  The patient experienced the booster dose on 17sep2021 with outcome of unknown, vasculitis on 01Oct2021 with outcome of unknown, intracranial hypertension on 20Oct2021 with outcome of unknown, small vessel ischemic changes on 01Oct2021 with outcome of unknown, body aches on 17Sep2021 with outcome of recovered on 18Sep2021, headache/ migraine on 17Sep2021 with outcome of not recovered.     The clinical course was reported as follows: She had her 3rd dose on Friday, 17Sep2021, and with her other two vaccines she had the normal side effects like body aches, headache, chills and low grade fever. Everything went away in 24 hours and it was no biggie. She thought that she just had a strong immune system but then with the 3rd dose she had it in the morning and went to work and then before her shift had ended she had body aches and a headache as well. 24 hours afterwards her body aches went away but she has had a pretty severe headache/ migraine ever since and it has never gone away. It doesnt come and go, it has been there all day every day, and it is constant. It has been 6 weeks. The side effects after her 3rd dose started in less than 8 hours afterwards.  She did get her pneumonia shot that Monday before she got her COVID vaccine, confirmed to be on 13Sep2021. Her physician said that it was fine to do them that closely spaced and the caller didnt think that anything was wrong with. In this whole journey of trying to figure this out because she has has no history of having headaches or migraines, she ended up having a CT scan and then she also had 1 MRI that showed possible intracranial hypertension and then she had a 2nd MRI that was looking for blood clots, there wasnt any, but it also showed intracranial hypertension. She has no history of hypertension and she actually has to take medications to keep her blood pressure up. Inquired for further details on the medications that she has to take to keep her blood pressure up and she states that she has Addisons disease and takes hydrocortisone as well as fludrocortisone because it also helps keep her electrolytes in balance to help maintain her blood pressure, she started them both 20 years ago. Inquired for dates of the CT scan and the 2 MRIs and she states that her had her 2nd MRI she believes on 27Oct2021 and the 1st on 20Oct2021 and both showed the intracranial hypertension. Her 1st MRI was with and without contrast. Now she is waiting to see an eye doctor because they apparently can see it behind the eyes and she is going to do that in a week and a half and then she has to meet with a neurologist after that to maybe do an LP to drain spinal fluid to try to relieve the pressure in her brain. Inquired for results of her CT scan and she states that it didnt come back normal there were something about non specific changes but she needs to double check. The CT was without contrast and it says that there were scattered non-spatial subcortical in the bilateral frontal lobes greater than the expected age, nonspecific and then it also said there were early small vessel ischemic changes and vasculitis to include white mater changes consistent with migraines, but she has never had migraines in her entire life until 17Sep2021. In her mind these are all cute changes. She had her CT scan on 01Oct2021, Oct2021 was a very expensive month for her.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: IgA nephropathy; This is a literature report.   Inclusion of patients with kidney disease in COVID vaccine trials remains low. It is important to report association of disease exacerbation so that patients may undergo post vaccination monitoring. The authors hereby present a case of worsening IgA nephropathy temporarily associated with COVID vaccination. A 63-year-old female with past medical history of hypertension, psoriatic arthritis presented to the hospital with gross hematuria for 6 weeks starting 3 days after 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine. Her PCP had sent her to ER 5 days after onset of hematuria as had noted a creatinine (Cr) of 1.6 with 3+ protein and greater than 20 RBCs on urinalysis suspicious for nephritic syndrome. On review she had serum Cr of 0.5 about 4 months ago with no proteinuria or hematuria before. In the ER she was given antibiotics for urinary tract infection and outpatient referral for nephrology. She could not make the outpatient appointment and with continued gross hematuria for a month, she presented to the ER again where she was noted to have Cr of 10 mg/dl and urine protein:cr ratio of 7.3gm/gm. Renal imaging including CT urogram was normal. Renal biopsy showed IgA nephropathy, M1S0E0T1C1 with a fibrocellular crescent and acute tubular necrosis likely secondary to lyzed red cells in setting of multiple RBC casts in the tubules. She was put on 250 mg Solumedrol for 3 doses followed by 1 mg/kg of Prednisone with eventual downtrend in Cr to 4.5 in 15 days.  There have been 2 cases reported in literature with known IgA nephropathy who developed gross hematuria post COVID 19 vaccination. SARS- COV 2 vaccines use nucleoside modified purified mRNA which does elicit higher neutralizing antibody titre and strong cluster of differentiation response leading to production of several proinflammatory cytokines. Thus, there is a concern that vaccines might exacerbate immune mediated glomerular diseases. IgA1 is involved in the pathogenesis of IgA nephropathy and patients with IgA nephropathy have higher than normal IgA1 response to other vaccines like influenza. Also while studying the antibody response to COVID 19 illness patients with IgA nephropathy are known to express higher IgA response compared to IgG and IgM along with reports of concurrent worsening of the glomerulonephritis. Nephrologists should closely follow patients with IgA nephropathy to establish the frequency of disease activation post vaccination.  No follow-up attempts are possible; information about lot/batch number cannot be obtained. No further information is expected.; Sender's Comments: Linked Report(s) : US-PFIZER INC-202101562750 Same article/drug/ event; different patient.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The most concerning symptom I had was a 4 hour period of continual tachycardia and palpations with a heart rate ranging from 160 to 180 while lying in bed trying to sleep (I have never had tachycardia or palpitations before). It  began  about 11  hours after the vaccination.  It self-resolved after about 4 hours.  Prior to developing the tachycardia (about 8 hours vaccination, I developed severe chills (for approx 10 hours despite being wrapped in layers of clothing and tripled blankets and having the heater on), strong headache, diffuse myalgia, SOB, and significant fatigue (i.e. I am a runner and I could not walk from my bed to the bathroom- approx 10 feet- without having to stop and sit down on the floor to breath and then muster up enough energy to make it the additional 5 steps). . All symptoms self-resolved within 24 hours and then I felt completely returned to normal and back to baseline. as if nothing had ever happened.  I had no reaction to the initial vaccine other than a mildly  sore arm at the injection site.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: CONFIRMED CLINICAL VACCINATION FAILURE; CONFIRMED COVID-19 INFECTION; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 54-year-old male (age at time of vaccination: 53 years). The patient's weight was 204 (unit unspecified), and height was 177.8 centimeters. The patient's concurrent conditions included: alcohol use (one drink in a week), non-smoker, hypertension, hypothyroidism, coronary artery disease, and cancer- lymphoma (since 1995). The patient had no known allergies. The patient had no history of drug abuse, no illness at the time of vaccination, no past history of similar event, no adverse event after any previous vaccination(s), no history of allergy to vaccine, drug, or food, no pre-existing acute illness 30 days prior to vaccination, no history of hospitalization in last 30 days with cause, no family history of any disease (relevant to vaccination) or allergy. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of administration not reported, batch number: 1802072, and expiry: unknown) dose was not reported (single dose), 1 total, administered on 10-MAR-2021 at 12:00 to right deltoid (shoulder) for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid), Niacin (nicotinic acid), Nexium (esomeprazole magnesium), atorvastatin, lisinopril, metoprolol, and levothyroxine sodium for unknown indication.  On 06-NOV-2021 and 07-NOV-2021 (8 months post vaccination), the patient was exposed to the delta variant of the covid-19 virus after travelling and became infected. He was vaccinated and felt fine. The patient reported having a dry cough from the concomitant medication lisinopril. On 09-NOV-2021 (Tuesday), he took a test with the provided rapid test kits from J and J, which was negative for covid-19. He went to work on 10-NOV-2021 (Wednesday) and 11-NOV-2021 (Thursday), with no interactions with anyone and noticed a difference in the cough on Thursday (confirmed covid-19 infection). The patient's taste was also impacted. On 12-NOV-2021 (Friday) morning, he started getting congested, in the evening he lost his sense of smell when he noticed he didn't smell the candles in his room, and his congestion became more pronounced following which he re-tested with the provided rapid test kits from J and J which came out positive. On the same date (at night), he also had fatigue and very mild fever (99.2 Fahrenheit). On 12-NOV-2021, the patient underwent a coronavirus disease 19 polymerase chain reaction (COVID-19 PCR) test which was positive for covid-19 infection (confirmed clinical vaccination failure). At the time of reporting, the patient's congestion nearly resolved, slight cough and fatigue continued to improve and taste was reported as still intact. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient was recovering from confirmed covid-19 infection, and the outcome of confirmed clinical vaccination failure was not reported. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition). This case, from the same reporter is linked to 20211133630. This report was associated with product quality complaint: 90000202400.; Sender's Comments: V0 20211134630-COVID-19 VACCINE AD26.COV2.S-confirmed clinical vaccination failure. This event(s) is considered not related. The event(s) has a compatible/suggestive temporal relationship, is unlabeled, and has unknown scientific plausibility. There are other factors more likely to be associated with the event(s) than the drug. Specifically: SPECIAL SITUATIONS.

On 05-Nov-2021, the patient received a 0.5 mL dose of suspect INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE lot QFAA2154 expiry date 30-05-22 and on 24-Sep-2021 he also received a 0.5 mL dose of the same vaccine lot QFAA2108 expiry date 30-05-22 via intramuscular route in unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I tried to fill out the form on the computer, and it got to my age and froze and would no longer let me type anything on the form. In case you think I'm to old, my grandmother lived to 102 and her father lived to the age of 97. I've also outlived my mother by many years who was a smoker. I never smoked. Since the adverse problems, my cursive that I always rewarded me with complements has really gone bad and my printing is not much better. Shortly after I got the first dose of vaccine (Moderna) around 28 February or the first or second week of March, both in 2021, I started to awaken about 4am with horrible pain in my legs, side and all over my lower body. I've made an appointment with my orthopedic doctor thinking my knees needed draining, but he wisely sent me to get an MRI of the back. Mind you, I always took the first appointment offered, so I was not able to get the MRI until March 24, 2021. Doct  appointment on April 29, 2021 have me a cortisone injection at Surgery Center, and at least it helped my awakening at 4am. Then, however, I started to fall (8 times total) and I was not dizzy nor did I black out - I just fell.   So, the falls happened between March 19, 2021 and June 17, 2021. The eighth occurred around September, 2021 (I did not record the date) on my deck many weeks later after weeks of physical therapy (two times a week) until I went in for a left eye cataract surgery which was postponed during Covid 19, and that was done on September 21, 2021. While my blood pressure was always controlled by medication, it now is out of sight all the time and is partially controlled by telmisartan 80 mg, (everyday), Indapamide 1.25 mg (a water ill) 4 times a week, and 81 mg aspirin 3 times a week, and Simvastatin 10 mg every night. All my medicines, allergies, and surgues are enclosed on a separate sheet. I am the beneficiary and wife of a retired spouse.   I have had two MRI (back and brain), two CT scans (brain and sinus), EMG, VNG, two carotid artery exams and I say sinus because the one on the brain which was to show any bleeding, showed no blood, and neither did an MRI, but it showed a sinus infection which was worse on the MRI. I was having no symptoms except my nose ran 24/7 and nose drops stopped that. So, Doctor (the ENT doctor) ordered the VNG to see if it showed any balance issues but nothing showed any by that time the sinus infection could not be detected any longer. I also had lab work done at Medical Center and one other place I cannot now remember, but nothing was reported to me as unusual. The EMG ruled out Parkinson's Disease and Neuropathy.  I went from walking to having a walker and cane on each floor of my home in a manner of weeks. I now walk funny with small steps. I had to but new mattresses because the others were too high (also new) and I fell off the high one. I am fearful of stepping off a curve and I still have gait problems as I just saw Doctor (Neurologist) November 4, 2021 and had my second arterial duplex on November 5, 2021 (Cardiologist). I've slowed down a lot and it takes me a long time to dress and do things. My legs are very weak and I'm fearful of stepping down a curb on uneven pavement because it is difficult for me. Sometimes I feel very uncoordinated. I use car straps getting into and out of cars. A lot of my symptoms mimic Guillain-Barre, but by the time I was tested weeks had gone by, so no one can be positive, by they all say there is a strong possibility. Afterall, when I go the Monderna vaccine I never expected there to be a problem. However, my balance is still off so when you ask if it is a disability or permanent damage, at this point, I don't know because I still have gait problems and weak legs. There were three other patients who have the same symptoms as mine in just the one practice. And recently, I learned of a niece who is much younger and after getting antibodies intravenously (she had Covid) she experienced symptoms similar to mind. I don't know the ages of those three, or what they did about it, but I very much fear the booster vaccine now. I sometimes go to urinate and I can't and I have difficulty washing the bottom of my right foot or putting on pants on my right leg especially. There is a dent in the middle of my forehead that was not there before I got the vaccine and it was not there even after hitting my head when I fell. When speaking in sentences, I forget what I am going to say- but I usually think of it later. The dent just appeared one day. On advice book I read during COVID-19 told me to keep track of every medical visit. Best advice I ever read.   Problems and Surgeries  High Blood Pressure, Joint Pain in Back, fluid fills knees periodically and must be drained, basal & squamous cell carcinoma on skin especially face. Knees ongoing in 2021 - BP especially 2021.  2 Mitchell Bunionectomies - one around 1977 and one in the late seventies or early 80's by doctor who is retired.  Ethmold sinus operation - Aug. 1992.  Six Cortisone Injections in Back in the 70's or 80's - Pain in Back unbearable- Was sent to Physical Therapy after first three Injections and it brought me back to square one where I needed 3 more Injections. Doctor gave the the shots and he died in a motorcycle accident. After six Injections I was ok for a long time.  Two Moh's surgery on nose by two different doctors.  Knees drained periodically and cortisone injected into the knees - Doctor 2021-and before.  March 24, 2021- Before this date kept waking up around 4am with such pain in legs. On this date doctor ordered an MRI on back.  Partial Hysterectomy - 2006 - Doctor  Right Eye Cataract Surgery - 2013- Doctor- Hospital  Vein Insufficiency both legs - 2017 - Doctor  Hospitalized for possible reaction to penicillin - 2017  Hearing aids - both ears - September 26, 2014 - New ones September 17, 2021 (Rechareable)  Hospitalized for a possible kidney stone - June 2019 - Hospital  Ablation/Rhizotomy on back - Doctor- Surgery Center - February 15, 2018. Successful and no pain for several years.  On April 14, 2021 Doctor said my kidneys were normal but she sent me to doctor who agreed. After seeing him, he called me and put me on an antibiotic because I had an UTI, but said my blood pressure was not good. I went to see a Blood Pressure Specialist, a cardiologist. I'm allergic to almost all categories of blood pressure medications now to include a new nitrate med (headache and general malaise) though I am on telmisartan - which is sometimes good and sometimes bad.  March 24, 2021 - Before this date kept waking up around 4am with such pain in legs. Doctor ordered an MRI on back (which was performed on this date) which resulted in my getting a cortisone injections.  Cortisone Shot in back - April 29, 2021 Doctor - Surgery Center It ceased my being awaked but sometimes my legs and buttocks hurt until I have my morning coffee - pain is bearable throughout the day. Since March 19, 2021 I have fallen 8 times in March, April, 3 times in May, twice in June and once on the deck going into the house either in September or October (I did not write it down). I am neither dizzy or disoriented - I just fall and mostly towards my right side. Also, the last one in the house was bloody as my forehead near the brow line was cut and the blood dripped into my eyes. My husband usually has to come down from upstairs to lift me up because I cannot do it myself.  In July when I saw the neurologist I was filled with terrible anxiety and she suggested I call a psychiatrist. I was on two different beta-blockers at two different times, and finally ended up with Bystolic (a newer one). I sometimes stayed awake for 24 hours. I needed sleep and stopped taking the beta-blocker where the valsartan at the time made me feel horrible. I called Pharmacy and asked if beta-blockers were made with dye. She went to check and came back saying yes. That's when I stopped Bystolic and I am like a different person - no more anxiety.  On August 17 of 2021 I went to Physical Therapy twice a week and my Physical Therapist - I stopped for Cataract Surgery.  Left Eye Cataract Surgery - September 21, 2021 - Doctor Surgery Center.  Skin Cancer Body check every six months.  VGN Ordered by Doctor on Oct. 5, 2021 and performed Oct. 20, 2021 at the Neurology Office. Showed minor stuff related to age.  My daughter took me to see Doctor, September 13, 2021 a Uro-Gynecologist, because she thinks my getting up so many times during the night to urinate disrupts my sleep. I had a urine test and was given a "Foods to Avoid" list and I am to consider getting injections. Must call to see if they are talking about Botox as I don't believe I want Botox and they had mentioned it on a prior visit, but not they just say injections. I also should follow a low oxalate diet because of my kidney stone.  After pain in my legs and falling - I have had two cat scans of head to check for bleeding *there was none) but it did show a minor sinus infection, and also, two MRIs, one of the back and August 11, 2021, one of the brain, which showed the sinus infection got worse. The second cat scan showed that sinus infection getting better. I have used a nose rinse given to me by doctor. An EMG July 27, 2021 said no neuropathy and no Parkinson's though I do tremble. It was rather late to show Guillain-Barre Syndrome, but I took the appointments as they came available and I never expected a problem after getting the vaccine. I also had a carotid artery test July 28. 2021, and an arterial duplex November 5, 2021. The renal duplex did not show any blockages. The carotid doppler showed no significant blockages as well.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 36 or so hours after receiving the second dose of the COVID-19 Pfizer vaccine (vaccine given 8/14/21), 14 year old male patient awoke from sleep around 1am on 8/16/21 complaining of substernal chest pain that was 8/10 in severity without any associated shortness of breath, lightheadedness, palpitations, syncope, or other symptoms. The pain improved to 3/10 with Tylenol prior to presenting to the emergency department.
LAB_DATA: He presented to the Emergency Department 8/16AM after onset of chest pain. ECG was obtained and noted ST elevation and PR depression in the inferior leads. He was given motrin for pain with complete resolution of pain within handful of hours of pain onset. Troponin level was negative/undetectable. He did not have a friction rub or tachycardia or fever at that time. He was admitted for observation and repeat troponin level was in a detectable range but still normal. He had no recurrence of pain and was discharged later that day with a diagnosis of likely vaccine induced pericarditis versus a costochondritis. He followed up in Pediatric Cardiology clinic with me MD 11/18/21 and his ECG is now normal with no ST abnormalities, also further evidence that this was likely pericarditis, and we feel likely related to his vaccine. He has been doing very well clinically throughout and asymptomatic.
HISTORY: Born with congenital Horner's Syndrome on the left. No debilitating or chronic effects from this other than left eye ptosis. No other medical conditions.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My doctor's office told me to go to urgent care for chest tightening /pain. At urgent care my white blood cells, platelets and lympocytes all tested abnormally high. I am an extremely healthy person with no health conditions and my "numbers" from all my blood tests in the past are consistently stellar. I have the readings of several years on record. Most recent blood work (prior to incident) was done in Feb. 2021. I still have chest pain.  Urgent care told me I had to go to the emergency room. They did additional tests. Those tests did look better except for my globulin which was out of the healhty range (very slightly). It has never been out of range. I was allowed to go home after 6 hours of hospital/urgent care testing. I still have chest pain.

He reported his dry weight to be 220 lbs with discharge standing weight being 98.6 kg (217 lb). Patient desired to discharge and not want to be monitored for 24 hours on resumption of his home oral lasix. He was instructed to monitor weight daily and maintain a 2 liter fluid restriction.    # COVID-19 Patient weaned to room air after lasix administration and given lack of findings suggestive COVID-19 on initial imaging, decadron was not given while hospitalized. Did receive dose in the ED. Patient was also noted to be vaccinated with J&J vaccine.    # Abnormal CT of the Chest Pulmonary was consulted given findings on chest CT and recommended outpatient follow-up with no additional workup while hospitalized.    Although patient did not reports any dyspnea with ambulation, he was noted to have oxygen saturation <88% at times while ambulating. Given his desire to discharge without further attempts to wean with IV lasix, pulmonary rehab was consulted an patient was discharged on 2 liters of oxygen via NC with activity. Patient was discharged home in stable condition with discharge instructions provided.

Three weeks after my initial shot (late March 2021), I started to experience vertigo and a thrumming, vibrating sensation in my ears. The vertigo is not the room spinning-type but a bobbing up and down and side to side sensation as if one is on a boat. I continued with my 2nd vaccine shot the following week. The symptoms continue to this day, 7.5 months after my first vaccine shot. None of these symptoms existed prior to receiving the vaccine. Initially, I reached out to my GP in late April 2021 My GP ordered a complete blood work-up and suggested I schedule a visit to an ENT. All of the blood work came back normal. I saw an ENT in May 2021. The ENT initially prescribed a 10-day prednisone treatment along with a 30-day treatment of fluticasone.  Neither resolved the issue. The ENT then referred me to an audiologist who conducted a series of vestibular tests, all of which returned normal results. The tests done in July 2021. The ENT then recommended vestibular therapy. After 3 sessions the therapist terminated my therapy as she was unable to reproduce the symptoms based on the tests available to her. The therapy occurred in late August and early September 2021. In late August 2021, I visited my GP again for further guidance. Another round of blood work was ordered. My GP did notice that my left sinuses were clogged and prescribed a 10-day course of antibiotics and a 5-day course of prednisone. None of these resolved the vertigo or the thrumming sensation in my ears. All blood work came back normal. Upon returning to my GP in October 2021, my GP prescribed an MRI, which was completed in November 2021. I have yet to receive the results of the MRI. My GP also prescribed a 30-day alternating treatment of meclizine and clonazepam. This treatment is going with no meaningful impacts to date.
OTHER_MEDS: Metformin, Vitamin D, Finasteride, Valtrex, Sertraline, Multivitamin, L-Lysine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: We experienced a fridge temperature excursion which started on Sunday and continued until Wednesday morning when it was finally discovered. The temperature started to slowly rise from 46F to a top temperature of 54.14F on Wednesday when we transferred the vaccines to another fridge. Unfortunately, we had administered vials of both Pfizer (adult purple cap only) and Janssen on Monday and Tuesday before the problem was discovered Wednesday morning. No vials were administered on Wednesday.   On Sunday, starting around 11 am, the temperature started to rise. The min. temperature for Sunday was 44.24F and the max. temperature was 48.02F.  On Monday the min. temperature was 47.84F and the max. was 51.26F. The temperature was above 50.5 on Monday for about 4 hours and 30 minutes. The vaccines for Monday were taken out of the fridge around 8:45am and placed in a temperature-controlled courier up to our vaccination clinic. In total 1 vial of Janssen was pulled (lot # 1822809 - 2 doses administered, 3 wasted) and 3 vials pulled of Pfizer (lot # FF2587 - 13 doses administered, 5 wasted). With the Pfizer pulled 2 vials may have been pulled at the 8:45 am time and 1 vial may have been pulled mid-day.   Patient Information:  0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 2 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 2 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.5 JSN 1822809 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 1 0.5 JSN 1822809 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3   On Tuesday the min. temperature was 49.64F and the max. was 51.44F. The temperature was above 50.5 on Tuesday for about 8 hours and 2 minutes. The vaccines for Tuesday were taken out of the fridge around 8:45am and placed in a temperature-controlled courier up to our vaccination clinic. In total 1 vial of Janssen was pulled (lot # 1822809 - 3 doses administered, 2 wasted) and 2 vials pulled of Pfizer (lot # FF2587 - 9 doses administered, 3 wasted).   Patient Information 0.5 JSN 1822809 Dose: 1 0.5 JSN 1822809 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 3 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 2 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 2 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 1 0.5 JSN 1822809 Dose: 1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose:1 0.3 PFR FF2587 Dose: 2   On Wednesday min. temperature was 41.54 as the vaccines were transferred into a new fridge around 10:30am and the max. temperature was 54.14F. The temperature was only above 50.5 on Wednesday for about 3 hours and 2 minutes. No vials from the fridge were administered.  I reached out to both Janssen and Pfizer manufacturers and talked to their excursion team and their safety team to relay patient information. Regarding the Janssen doses administered, the documentation provided to me and relayed over the phone from Janssen was thus: ?47F to 50 F ? No restriction in duration if the product is not expired. For 51F to 77F ? Up to 12 hours (cumulative) if the product is not expired?. Our product is not expired and did not meet the ?Up to 12 hours cumulative? when we administered the vaccines. No further steps were taken to reach out to patients. We will dispose of the vaccines we have left in the fridge.   Regarding Pfizer, I submitted a report to their excursion team as well as submitted patient information to their safety team. I received an email stating they had no data regarding stability for the vaccine for the temperature excursion I reported and was directed to call the CDC. I called the CDC, but they said I would need to receive specific information about what to do for patients administered the vaccine from the manufacturer. The CDC also asked me to submit a VAERS report and to receive more information for the patients from VAERS. I am seeking guidance on whether the patients we vaccinated need to be re-vaccinated and what to tell them regarding the vaccination they previously received. Please advise.

At 0600,  20 hours after receiving the vaccine I arose from bed, like I always do, I took 2 steps and the next thing I remember is opening my eyes and my face was on my hand. I lost consciousness for 5-10 seconds. I fell headfirst into a piece of furniture. My forehead received a hard impact on the edge of a chest and a wound about 4 inches in length opened up over my L eye. I also hit my mouth and nose on the furniture and one of my front teeth became loose.    My ribs on both sides of my chest hit pieces of furniture as I fell forward. I was unable to do anything to break my fall. After a few seconds upon opening my eyes I realized where I was and a blinding pain seared into my awareness. The pain was so intense that I couldn't' move at first. I slowly got up while feeling a stream of blood falling on to my hand. I cleaned myself up and went to a local hospital. I didn?t feel dizzy or lightheaded when I stood up to go into my bathroom to look in the mirror at what had just happened.
LAB_DATA: I was admitted to hospital from the ER b/c of my age and my report of fainting.  Several 12 lead ECGs, Orthostatic Blood Pressures, CT of the Head, and CT of the thorax with contrast were performed also blood panels were drawn. There were no abnormalities except some minor blood derangements. Blood glucose at 10:30 AM Tuesday 11/16 was 103mg/dcl, high  MCH 31.5 high, Lymph % 13.2% low, D-Dimer, High Sens 1.85 UG/ML FEU High, Anion gap 4mmol/L Low, Troponin- I level 3ng/L Low, BUN/Create Ratio 8.5 Low, UA Leuk Est- Trace- Abnormal. I am scheduled for a echocardiogram on Monday 11/22? No one can tell me what happened. Why did I suddenly loose consciousness? That it was a reaction to the COVID Moderna vaccine can neither be proved or unproved. Does this fit any profile of reactions to the vaccine thus far reported? I don?t? know. However I thought it was the responsible thing to do to report it myself and describe as much as I could to add to the body of knowledge for this vaccine.

I had a Moderna vaccination. After about 40 minutes I was experiencing severe shortness of breath and dizziness. At the time I thought is was normal as from what I have read. It went away in a few hours. Two weeks later I went to get my second shot and they wouldn't administer as I told them what my reaction was.   July 23, I experienced a very sharp stabbing-like sensation in my heart region. I was not able to breathe as well. We called emergency call they came in did an EKG, and said everything looked OK. After some time the sensation went away, but we still decided to go to ER and see what was that horrible feeling. ER ran a full blood test along with chest xrays and Troponin istat. They said that there no no sign of a heart attack. The next day I was not able to walk at all. I simply could breathe normally. Sharp stabbing pinching pain in my heart region would not go away. I made an appt with my physician. He was told me that he thinks I have MYOCARDITIS inflammation of the heart and referred me to go see a cardiologist. It took me a long time to make an appt with a cardiologist. at this point its been over 2 months. i could not walk for no more than 20 min before I had to completely stop and nothing was going away. The doctor told me we need to do 3 tests to rule out Myocarditis. ECHO, STRESS TEST, AND HOLTER. after those tests were done the doctor couldn't catch anything so he suggested a 4 test TELEMETRY monitor a device I have connected to me for 7 days and I would press the button when symptoms arise. Three and a half months later the doctor has fully diagnosed me with MYOCARDITIS due to induced vaccination of modern. I am officially exempt from vaccination now. It has been 4 months. I actually reported to you guys once before I got a call from a lady, I returned her call she never got back to me . I am shocked and baffled that she didn't. I have suffered through hell during this time and MY  guess wasn't even properly documented. I am reaching out again as you should document this officially. MYOCARDITIS IS SERIOUS AND COULD CAUSE DEATH AND PERMANANT HEART DAMAGE.
