On 4/14/2021 at about 4:00PM, I started experiencing painful muscle spasms in my left calf. I tried to get rid of the pain by walking it off and scratching my leg, but the more I walked, the worse it got. I don't like taking a lot of medicines, so I took 81mg of aspirin. I waited and the pain eased a bit. I also had hot ginger tea with lemon and honey and hoped it would help me relax a bit. I then prepared dinner and later went to bed. I woke up at about 3:00-3:30AM on 4/15/2021 to go to the bathroom and noticed the pain was returning, so I took a hot shower and hoped it would help the muscles relax. I then went back to bed and woke up at 8:30AM. I went to get breakfast and noticed the pain had returned and was even worse than it had been at 3:00AM, so I took some more aspirin. The pain eased a bit and I was able to go on with my day. On 4/16/2021, the pain returned and was so bad that I could hardly walk. I tried to find someone to take me to the ER, but I couldn't find anyone, so I made do by taking aspirin every 6-8 hours to help ease the pain. On 4/17/2021, my sister called me and asked if I was still in pain. I told her I was, so she took me to the ER at Memorial Hospital. The ER staff told me I had probably pulled or injured a muscle, though I hadn't done anything to injure my leg. They wrapped my leg in a tight bandage and advised me to rest and to try to refrain from using my leg as much as possible. However, I found that the bandage made the pain worse, so I removed the bandaged and tried elevating my leg. Over the following 2 weeks, I continued to experience leg pain and swelling. On 4/30/2021, I went to Health for an upper endoscopy. They noticed my leg was swollen and asked if I was in pain, and I told them I was. They decided not to perform the endoscopy and had me wheeled over to the ER. At the ER, I underwent tests, and they found a blood clot. I was promptly given Eliquis and was kept until about 5:00 PM, so they could monitor me and ensure the medicine was working. They gave me a week's supply of Eliquis and told me to go to my PCP to get another prescription for Eliquis when I ran out. I tried to get in to see my regular PCP, but he was booked solid, so I switched to another doctor, who has been following my case ever since. I am currently still taking Eliquis, and I no longer experience the pain I did before I started taking it. I am scheduled to see doctor on 12/1/2021, and he plans to check to see if the clot has dissolved.
OTHER_MEDS: Albuterol inhaler (as needed) Prescription vitamin D3 (50, 000 IU) once a week Creon (36,000 IU) two capsules 3 times a day before meals Centrum Women's Multivitamin OTC Calcium supplement (600 mg) Prescription vaginal Estrogen cream

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On November, 4th, I received a COVID booster shot. The reaction to shot number 3 was less than expected on the day of the shot and for the next two days. I did not feel ill, just very tired. Although, I was not as tired as with shot number 2. About a week after receiving the COVID booster shot, I noticed that the the pain and stiffness I have from osteoarthritis was getting worse. I have flare up pain and stiffness occasionally so I did not think much of it and it only lasts a few days. However, this time the pain flare up kept getting worse and is still ongoing. I contacted my Primary Care Doctor and asked her advice on 11/15. She indicated that to her knowledge, arthritis flare up from COVID vaccination occurred within a couple days of the injection. She advised that I wait another week and take the maximum amount of Tylenol per day to relieve some of the pain. If there was no improvement in the pain and stiffness, to come in to see if something else was going wrong. I have been taking the maximum safe amount of Tylenol since then and I do have less pain and stiffness, but I cannot tell if the reduced pain is a result of gradual improvement or from taking the Tylenol.  I don't know for sure that the increased pain and stiffness is a result of the COVID vaccine or not. The vaccine injection is the only thing that I have done differently than my routine activities for the past three weeks.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the 2nd dose at around 3pm.  About 12 hours later I woke up from my sleep and felt feverish, headachy, uncomfortable, and sick. I felt like I got hit by a truck. I had no energy. That feeling persisted all throughout the next day on 5/20/2021. I sat on my couch and didn't move that whole day. After that I was able to sleep better. I still felt achy and weak on 5/21/2021, but by 5/22/2021 I felt normal and back to myself.  2 days after getting the vaccine I was really knocked out. On 9/10-12/2021 I went on a backpacking trip in the wilderness. I had drank filtered surface water. On 9/19/2021 I began having intestinal issues. It started off with horrible diarrhea that lasted about 12 hours then the diarrhea had went away, but then I had constipation, bloating, and cramping that was uncomfortable but not severe. I was really uncomfortable for 2 days and moderately uncomfortable for 2 weeks. Just now I am starting to feel normal after a couple of months. I had went to the doctor's office and had tests did that were all negative. I started doing dietary changes, specifically with gluten. There seems to be some type of gluten sensitivity but I'm not for sure.

Patient received booster dose of Moderna vaccine in left arm at around 10:03 am on Friday, 11/19/21. A few minutes after vaccine administration patient complained of "weird metallic taste" in her mouth and was offered a bottle of water. After a few sips of water patient complained of a "tingling sensation" down left arm. Patients BP was checked and was 148/99. patient was then escorted upstairs to  see nurse practitioner. I am unsure what tests/laboratory results were completed. As patient was coming down the steps she said she "hurt all over and was nauseated". Patient was helped down the stairs were she said she felt lightheaded and was having trouble breathing. Nurse practitioner listened to patient and said she was starting to wheeze and needed epinephrine. Pharmacist (me) called emergency number and administered 0.3 mg of epinephrine via auto injector. Patient began to shake all over and said she was still struggling to breath. patient was given 25 mg of liquid benadryl. The nurse then brought a solu medrol shot and administered it to patient in hip. Ambulance arrived a few moments later and took patient to Hospital.
LAB_DATA: BP, PULSE OX, others unknown contact Healthcare for more info.

My first adverse event I had muscle and body aches and joint pains. It was all over my body and I couldn't sleep. I had a low-grade fever; I had a sore arm where I got the injection on the right arm. I put my symptoms in the questionnaire. I would take Tylenol every 6 hours and drink water. I spoke to my doctor via email. I was unable to perform my schoolwork, due to being in a lot of pain. I tried to rest as much as I could. This was mainly the issues, and this was on the 27th. On the 28th I was able to return to school, but my muscle and body aches were still hurting. I'm not sure how it long it lasted, but I did put it in the questionnaire. It did last for a few days. I had some aches in my hips and legs. It wasn't as bad as the day of my injection. I was mainly taking the acetaminophen. This past Monday on Nov 15 I had the same symptoms minus the fever, The pain and soreness returned in my neck and my upper shoulder blade. Then both arms it felts like I got injections. My neck was really sore, and it felt like I got the shot all over again. I took some Tylenol and I had to go to school. I thought I was getting a virus, but my temperature was normal. I took a muscle relaxer, but nothing helped. I called my nurse advisor on Monday and used a heating pad. They told me to use an ice pack, she suggested Motrin, but I didn't use it due to it hurting my stomach. They made an appointment to see my doctor Tuesday 16. Doctor offered more muscle relaxers and offered Lidocaine patches.  I've been using heating pads and lidocaine cream. I've been using muscle relaxer about every six hours and the pain is getting better. The pain is mainly only on my neck and right between my shoulder blades.  I've been using some essential oils to help with the pain.
OTHER_MEDS: I was taking Acetaminophen 500mgs, I took it every 6 hours for a few days.

Patient immediately felt ill after administration of the second dose of Pfizer. Patient felt dizzy, nauseous, had blurry vision and could not hear for a few moments. Patient complained that her nose got congested and that her eyes felt extremely heavy and she felt extremely lethargic. Patient did not lose conscientiousness at any time. We immediately put her to sit next to her father in the waiting area, applied an ice pack to her neck and gave her some water.  We continued to talk to her to keep her awake and alert. Father asked that we call the paramedics which we did and in the meantime prior to their arrival we continued to engage the patient in conversation.  She had no difficulty breathing at any time. Paramedics came, we informed them of the event and they offered to take the patient in for medical attention.  The father and daughter both declined transport via ambulance to the hospital.  After about 30 minutes, the patient was better, the symptoms for the most part had subsided and she was able to stand up and walk out with her father.

Started experiencing slight racing heart starting around 8:30pm day of vaccination (Wednesday the 27th of Jan) but went to bed as normal. Woke up at 1am with heart racing uncomfortably and shortness of breath, felt light-headed when standing and walking. Pulse oximeter reading at home was between 120-140 bpm. Called advice nurse, was told to either go to ER immediately or could wait 30 minutes to see if it improved. After 20 minutes no improvement, so admitted self into ER around 2am. Was told EKG appeared normal except for elevated heart rate. Began to develop throbbing headache around 3-4am. Given Benadryl and Tylenol and kept to wait for blood test results until about 5:30am. During this time heart rate decreased and headache subsided and was sent home. The next 2 days continued to feel very fatigued and experiencing shortness of breath with daily self-care activities. Returned to work on Monday (4 days after vaccination) and able to resume normal activities at work. One week following vaccination was still continuing to experience shortness of breath with light-moderate exercise (walking up slightly inclined hill). One month later continued noticing shortness of breath symptoms with moderate exercise. 6 months later experienced 3 instances of tightness in chest (felt like a panic attack almost) when driving.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Developed Bell's Palsy. Symptoms began with some loss of taste on the evening of 07/12/2021. On the morning of 07/13/2021, I was still experiencing the loss of taste but also had pain along the jaw near the bottom of my right ear. Woke up with malaise and pain in left (surgical) breast. Malaise progressed to brain fog, fatigue, and muscle aches over a 5-6 day period. Left breast swelled and turned red. Saw primary physician on 10/8/21 and was prescribed antibiotics and an emergency visit was scheduled with Dr. and PA, at Breast Center on 10/11/21.  At 4:00 am 10/11/21, woke with massive spontaneous drainage of left breast. Dr. diagnosed radiation recall vs lymphedema of the breast. An ultrasound was performed. A wick was inserted into the open wound to allow for additional drainage. The wick was replaced several times before finally fallilng out on 10/30/21. The spontaneous wound subsequently closed up. The breast then became concave on the left side at the site of the lumpectomy cavity/ surgical scar area. The initial erythema had subsided somewhat but the area around the scar remained red. Dr. gave a referral to another Dr for evaluation of left breast lymphedema. Dr. indicated this was the third case she had seen of breast lymphedema following Covid vaccine injections. She again prescribed antibiotics plus physical therapy to enhance range of motion and release scar tissue that has formed in the surgical area. The indentation from the collapsed seroma cavity will not go away and the breast will remain smaller than the other breast and possibly require plastic surgery in the future. This is permanent disfigurement and has rightfully caused quite a bit of distress to the patient.
LAB_DATA: left breast ultrasound 10/18/21 which was negative for any abscess or additional seroma pocket within the previous lumpectomy cavity
OTHER_MEDS: anastrozole, calcium, vitamin d3, citalopram, fish oil
CUR_ILL: glucosamine, kevothyroxine, metformin, metoprolol, omeprazole, simvastatin
HISTORY: benign essential hypertension, hyperlipidemia, hypothyroidism, gerd, left breast cancer, osteoarthritis, osteopenia,  anxiety, prediabetes

Over the next day, these two things would contine.  Severe chills and fever.   I couldn't eat.  I couldn't drink.  I couldn't watch tv or read a book.  All I could do was either sleep or sit in a chair staring out into space.  Even today, my mind is not very clear.   Today I also have a constant need to pee.  Even after I basically haven't had much water or any other liquid since Wednesday.  After my 2nd shot, also Pfizer, I had very similar side effects but not as severe.   Today, right now, Friday, 11/19/21 at 3:00 pm my temperature is 101.2.
CUR_ILL: Swelling of the left ankle.  Unknown reason.
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer Covid shot #2.  Same as shot #3 but not as severe.

Patient received his vaccine on Tuesday, by Wednesday early evening he presented with low energy, but otherwise good spirits.  By 7pm when his temp was taken he had a 104.7 degree temp.  Cognitives were good, mood was good.  Dose of Children's 10ml (320mg) Tylenol at 7pm and again at 12am (Thursday Morning).  Thursday 7:30am Morning temp rested at 103.5.  Another dose of Children's 10ml Tylenol (320mg) at 7:30am and fever began to wane over the course of the day.  Again Children's 10ml Tylenol  (320mg) at Thursday 4pm temp was 102.6.    At 9pm on Thursday patient's voice started to become raspy, but was still in good mood.  Again, Children's 10ml Tylenol (320mg) at 12am (Friday).  Friday Morning 7:30am  temp was resting at 99.0, however patient was having a hard time breathing and his voice was significantly worse.  Patient presented with a dry cough and difficulty catching breath.  The cough was like Croup, deep in chest, and reverberated through esophagus.    He was given another does of Children's 10ml Tylenol  (320mg) Friday at 7:30am, and a 5ml of Infant Ibuprofen (200mg) for throat swelling, and one dose of Albuterol Inhaler (90 mcg) to alleviate difficulty breathing.  We then practiced breathing exercises to calm him down, which worked fairly well.  His coughing subsided, and we administered 5ml Children's Cough DM (30mg dextramethorphan hydrobromide) to suppress coughing.  By 2:15pm (now) his voice has started to come back, but is still raspy and he feels better.
LAB_DATA: None, just the injection of the Covid Vaccine

Developed a small blood clot in my right lung. Initial symptoms started on Mon. 6/7/21. Felt like indigestion. Started early afternoon. Did not take anything that day (may have had some tea). Next day slight increase in symptoms. Took acid-indigestion medicine early afternoon followed by muscle relaxant followed by one (1) Aleve Muscle and Back pain tablet (these were all taken hours apart). Note: I work from home; shift ends at 2am. Symptoms did not subside but increased by that evening. By end of shift, was experiencing intense pain in chest area that hurt whether sitting, standing, bending over, laying down or moving. included shortness of breath. Tried to sleep and eventually got up around 7am on 6/9/21 and decided to go to nearest ER. Managed to get dressed and took Uber to ER. Was admitted to ER as soon as I arrived. Received ECG, blood pressure test, chest x-ray, covid test, chest MRI scan (w/ and w/o contrast), ultra sound of the legs, TTC w/ doppler and color, and various blood tests. The testing revealed the small blood clot in my right lung. Was admitted into the hospital and given Eliquis (oral, tablets) for that day and next and prescribed prescription for initially one month. I informed my cardiologist, my primary doctor and  neurologist of what was happening. Was eventually given a prescription by primary doctor for three (3) month supply of Eliquis and referral to hematologist by attending physician at ER and cardiologist to find out if I was susceptible to blood clots as there is not a known history of this in my family. Returned to the ER two times afterwards (6/18 - not admitted and 6/23 - admitted) for additional pain and shortness of breath. Was given an ECG, blood tests, blood pressure test, chest x-rays for both. Was given a chest CAT scan on the 6/23 visit. It was discovered during this visit that the blood clot had dissolved. On 6/24, was given a stress test by my cardiologist (he is affiliated with this hospital). Passed. Saw Hematologist in 8/2021; returned for results on 9/13/21. No propensity was found for blood clots. Conclusion - clot resulted from vaccine. Informed that I could stop taking Eliquis at end of month.  I did return to the ER just recently (11/10/21) due to the same/similar symptoms that I experienced back in June 2021 (heaviness in chest area). Similar test given (ECG, blood pressure, blood tests, chest x-ray, and chest MRI (w/ and w/o contrast). Also received pain meds and muscle relaxant (given before MRI in case this was muscle related). Results indicated no new blood clots, some small cysts in right lung.
LAB_DATA: See Item #18 Continuation Page for tests, dates and most results.  Complete copies of tests and results available upon request.
OTHER_MEDS: Gilenya; Hydrochlorothiazide; Metoprolol Succ Er; Oxbutynin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 69-year-old female, status post Covid vaccine booster with subsequent arthralgias, headache and fever.  She developed dyspnea and was evaluated in the emergency department for this.  She had extensive evaluation including D-dimer which was elevated and subsequent CT chest for pulmonary embolus.  Care transferred to me at change of shift awaiting CT results.   On reevaluation she is resting comfortably.  She had spontaneous return of dyspnea with no subsequent difficulty breathing.  She still has a residual headache.  Labs reviewed with the significant abnormality.  Vital signs are stable.  She is well-appearing and resting comfortably.   CT chest negative for pulmonary embolus.  There is an incidental finding of a 4 mm nodule in the right apex which is thought to have benign appearance and recommendation per radiology is either no follow-up or 1 year follow-up depending on risk factors.  This is discussed with her and she will be following up with her primary care physician to discuss the need for repeat imaging and plan accordingly.   Further treatment and indications for return are reviewed.  Good understanding.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: While I was working, a lady came to the counseling window to ask a question. She told me she had gotten a Johnson and Johnson COVID shot ten minutes before and stated her arms felt numb, tingly, and heavy. She asked whether this normal.  I told her it?s not a normal, common side effect. I asked her if she had a history of reactions to vaccinations. She told me she hadn?t. I asked her for her name and phone number so I can report it to VAERs.  She then complained of sudden numbness in her upper lip. I realized it might be an allergic reaction. I grabbed a chair and had her sit down. I then got an epipen and went into the office to tell a manager to call 911.  I went back to check on the customer and asked how she was doing. She stated her throat was starting to tingle. I noticed upper lip was starting to swell. I asked her if she could wait for the paramedics to arrive, but she asked me to give her the epipen shot. She mentioned she got an epipen shot when she young. She didn?t know what she?s allegoric to, but this wasn?t the first time she was given an epipen shot.  I gave her the shot. She started feeling better, and I gave her some water and some candy because she appeared to be in a state of low-sugar. The paramedics arrived shortly after this. I explained the situation to the paramedics and what I had done for the customer.  Leaving the customer in the care of the paramedics, I went back to the pharmacy. She left with the paramedics shortly after this.
ALLERGIES: Yes , but she does not remember

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the vaccine at 5:00 PM 11/12/21. I woke on 11/13/21 with  body aches and fatigue. at around 2:30 PM on 11/13/21 I developed a low-grade frontal headache and low-grade fever of 99.7 F. This persisted through the evening. At 8:00 I still had it. I went into the kitchen to get some soup, and while standing at the counter suddenly felt lightheaded and nauseated. I yelled NO NO NO and started to go down. The next thing I knew my poor husband was standing over me and I thought I was in bed! He told me that I had fallen and twisted my leg really badly. I told him I needed to go to the bathroom. I made it there then proceeded to have diarrhea and vomiting. I was also sweating profusely. After that I rested and those symptoms resolved, BUT I sustained a pretty substantial sprain strain to my left medial collateral ligament, my entire right knee, and my right foot and lateral ankle. It hasn't prevented me from working (I'm a physician) but it has prevented me from riding my bike, my chosen and favorite form of exercise! So, I had an episode of vasovagal syncope.  I think it's noteworthy that a little before the event I took about 35 mg of CBD. CBD can cause a sudden drop in blood pressure which can lead to syncope, nausea and vomiting

I started to have fever and chills about 6-7 hours after receiving the Moderna booster. I went to sleep in the evening and woke in the middle of the night with severe chills, sweating, headache, nausea, and a feeling of rigidity in the muscles of my forearms and wrists, with involuntary contraction of my hands. I wasn't in a condition to check my temperature with a thermometer. I took two aspirin, drank some cold water, and the chills improved and the muscle rigidity and hand contraction went away. I continued to have chills, headache and nausea return every 4-6 hours, into the next day, which I alleviated with 1-2 aspirin during each interval. By the next afternoon, about a day after receiving the booster, I was feeling subjectively much better and measured my temperature with an oral thermometer: it was 102 Fahrenheit. Two days subsequently, I noticed a palpable left axillary lymph node, which persisted for another 2-3 days. Altogether, these symptoms were similar but to a worse degree than what I experienced after the second dose of the Pfizer vaccine nine months earlier. However, the fever seemed higher and came on faster; the muscle rigidity/hand contraction, and axillary lymphadenopathy were new symptoms.

Had covid booster and flu shot at work and 4 hours later began to have progressive fatigue, chills, confusion, dysarthria, echolalia, dyskinesia, emesis and was taken to the ER. In the ER she was found to be hypotensive and febrile to 39.2 with tachycardia. Her psychiatric symptoms resolved with lorazepam, toradol and acetaminophen. She was admitted for ongoing care as she remained hypotensive requiring norepinephrine.   With remote teratoma 2015 s/p resection and no e/o recurrence I wonder if her COVID (and/or influenza) vaccinations reactivated a senescent paraneoplastic syndrome. Her prodromal headache, fever and dysautonomia have now been complicated by two prolonged episodes of anxiety, agitation, psychosis, dyskinesias, diminished language output and echolalia which are concerning for an encephalitis like picture. Her dramatic improvement after high dose lorazepam with complete normalization of neuropsychiatric symptoms but not all autonomic symptoms is puzzling. Her symptoms are not typical for anxiety attacks. She was responsive enough during the episodes to argue strongly against generalized seizures. CT abd/pelvis did not show recurrent mass. Procalcitonin negative, arguing against systemic bacterial infection/sepsis. Her symptoms are too delayed to attribute to anaphylaxis to vaccinations.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1. Pressure and pain in left arm, sudden onset 3 days after second dose, ongoing intermittent. 2. Numbness and tingling "funny-bone" sensation from left forearm through left index finger. 3. "Pins and needles" tingling, numbness and pain in both feet and sometimes lower legs, four days after second dose. Ongoing intermittent. May subside for many hours or a few days, then flare up again. Symptoms worse in left foot. 4. Aching pain in bottoms of both feet when walking. 5. Sometimes "pins and needles" sensation will fire randomly at various locations over the body. 6. Fluctuating resting HR and BP. * Contacted my PCP 15 days after second dose and 11 days into symptoms. Teleconference with PCP prompted concerns over the possibility of Guillaine Barre Syndrome and immediate referral to neurologist at Hospital. Complete and thorough exam by both healthcare provider and attending Neurologist found no signs of muscle weakness, paralysis or muscle weakness. Was given additional signs and symptoms of GBS to watch for and instructed to report to Emergency if any signs of facial drooping or foot/leg weakness paralysis occurred. Advised to discontinue Zinc supplementation to see if that reduces "pins and needles" sensation and left arm/foot numbness and pain. Almost no symptoms during bed rest/sleep.
OTHER_MEDS: Z-Pac 250 mg, Vit-C: 500mg, D3:2000 IU, E:180mg, Mag 250mg, Zinc:50 mg.

COVID Breakthrough  Pfizer Dose 1 1/21/21 (lot not listed in IRIS/ICARE) Pfizer Dose 2 2/10/21 (lot not listed in IRIS/ICARE) COVID Positive 8/23/21  8/23/21: The patient is an 89-year-old female presents to the emergency department today via EMS from Nursing Home with altered mental status, increasing drowsiness and lethargy.  The patient has a past medical history significant for chronic UTI on prophylactic trimethoprim, neuropathy, hyperlipidemia, obesity, anxiety, mitral valve prolapse, and is bed-bound requiring hoyer lift for transfers.   On arrival to the ED, the patient's temperature is 98.5� F, heart rate 104, respiratory rate 18, saturating 93% on room air with blood pressure 155/101.  Later patient satting 88% on room air requiring 2 L supplemental O2 to maintain sats greater than 90%.  Patient's laboratory studies were significant for glucose 150, ALT 35, AST 44, troponin negative, mg 1.7, urinalysis with 15 ketonuria, moderate hematuria, rare bacteria, 1-3 pyuria, 1-3 RBCs. CT chest shows no acute intrathoracic process, mildly torturous aorta, prior granulomatous disease with scattered calcified granulomas in the lungs and calcified mediastinal and hilar lymph nodes.  CT head shows no acute intracranial findings with age-related volume loss and bilateral white matter disease likely consistent with chronic microangiopathic changes.  Chest x-ray shows abnormal cardiomediastinal silhouette likely secondary to tortuous ectatic thoracic aorta and mild pulmonary venous congestion.  EKG shows sinus tachycardia with PACs, right bundle-branch block and inferior T-waves in inferior leads, heart rate 106, QTC 486. Patient administered NS IV 500 mL in Zofran 4 mg IV in the emergency department.   The patient was seen in the emergency department laying in bed with her son at the bedside.  The patient was very lethargic and unable to arouse/keep awake, but would grimace or grown to painful stimuli.  The patient is currently on 2 L supplemental O2 via nasal cannula and saturating in the 90s.  The patient's son reports that she is bed-bound at baseline and they have to use a lift to get her up.  She is a DNR/DNI status.  8/25/21: Patient is admitted hospital, neuro checks performed per protocol, her mental status has improved, has some baseline cognitive deficits and has remained stable. Stroke workup done with the carotid Doppler and echocardiogram is unremarkable.  She does not have any new neurological deficits.  Patient has been febrile in the hospital, her COVID-19 test is positive.  Inflammatory markers ordered, pretty unremarkable.  Chest x-ray negative for infiltrate.  Admission patient was placed on oxygen as she was noted to have 1 episode of hypoxia with pulse ox 88%.  Oxygen has been weaned off and the patient has remained on room air, no further hypoxia noted.  Patient does not need any treatment for COVID-19 at this time as there is no hypoxia on inflammatory markers are at baseline.  She is discharged back to the long-term care facility in stable condition.  Continue Tylenol and the adequate oral hydration.  Monitor pulse ox and the transfer the patient back to ED if hypoxia noted.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Prior to the vaccination I did not have HBP. Several weeks after vaccination, around 03/01/2021, I was going to routine doctor appointment and I notice my BP was suddenly high.  The BP was up and down for a month and a half after the vaccine. My blood pressure was very high 160/98.  I went to see a Cardiologist and he immediately said I had HBP and put me on medication. He sent me for a bunch of test.  My BP was spiking up and down. I thought it was white coat syndrome or the tightness of the cuff.  I did not want to take my HBP medication. I was afraid to take the medication when my BP was very low. I did not know what was going on. The doctor suggested I track my BP for two weeks. The results were suggested I did not have HBP. After I had the 3rd booster vaccine, a couple of weeks later I had the same HBP results again-190/105. It was worse after the 3rd dose, instead of spiking up and down. It was spiking up.  I have a heart murmur that I did not have before.

The patient has a past medical history significant for COPD, chronic hypoxic respiratory failure on continuous 2-3 liter/minute supplemental O2, history of pneumonia, and history of smoking-quit.  Of note, patient follows with pulmonology outpatient and has been calling office for COPD exacerbation treatment every month, given prednisone burst on 06/22, 7/20, and Z-Pak on 08/11.  Patient fully vaccinated with Moderna COVID-19 vaccine.  On arrival to the ED, the patient's temperature is 101.4� F, heart rate 91, respiratory rate 19, saturating 86% on 5 L supplemental O2 via nasal cannula subsequently requiring increased oxygen at 7 L, then BiPAP mask with blood pressure 122/86 and 6/10 severity chest pain with cough.  The patient's laboratory studies were significant for COVID-19 rapid AG positive, Na 133, mg 1.5, CRP 4.8, D-dimer 0.62 age adjusted normal.  Blood cultures obtained x2.  Chest x-ray shows unchanged scarring at right lung base in airspace disease or atelectasis at left lung base.  CT chest shows mild interstitial thickening and ground-glass opacification compatible with viral pneumonia; right upper lobe nodule seen on prior exam resolved; centrilobular emphysema.  EKG shows normal sinus rhythm, heart rate 96, QTC 439 with left anterior fascicular block and nonspecific ST abnormality. The patient was administered acetaminophen 650 mg p.o., NS IV x1 L, levofloxacin 750 mg IV, Decadron 6 mg IV, DuoNeb 6 mL, and albuterol 6 mL in the emergency department. The patient is seen in the emergency department laying in bed currently on 7 L supplemental O2 via nasal cannula with BiPAP at the bedside.  The patient reports he started feeling bad on 08/09.  He reports that 1 of his roommates has been difficult to convince to get vaccinated and he believes that he likely was exposed from him.  He does have a history of positive sputum culture with Pseudomonas in the past.  He is frustrated that he was fully vaccinated and is now hospitalized with COVID-19, we did discuss that his frequent prednisone prescriptions could have made him more immunosuppressed and we have seen more COVID-19 in fully vaccinated patient's who were immunosuppressed.  8/23/21: PT was admitted and given treatment for COVID pneumonia with with IV antibiotics, steroids, bronchodilator therapy. Patient is a foreign exchange student staying with a local host family. When the patient and host family were asked for a birthday down at the drop off window it was inputted to make the patient 18 years old. Once the paper work was filled out it had a different birth year than originally given making patient 15 instead. The pharmacist went to double check with host parent (child speaks very little English) for age (as this was an 18 and up Moderna vaccine) and it appeared they believed the birthdate given at the drop off window was correct and not birth year on consent form and pharmacist notated that birth year onto the PQCF. The host parent was asked at 2nd visit (28 days later) if this may have been possible and they said there was confusion on birthdate originally but the birthdate making patient 15 was the correct birthday. On second visit host parent was informed what happened and that pfizer would need to be given to complete series instead of Moderna. They understood and were fine with that. Host parent was also asked if the child experienced any side effects from the dose of moderna and none had been noted. Host parent was very kind and understanding. They waited patiently while we made some calls and double checked CDC guidance. They did not mention any upset or anger and stated they were grateful patient was able to complete series. They were informed if patient would qualify for booster eventually, current recommendations would be to continue with pfizer.
Congestive heart failure and phenmona.
HISTORY: Borderline high blood pressure, hep C Tuburulous.
ALLERGIES: No known Allergies, besides hay fever and seasonal allergies.

Prior to the vaccination, my blood pressure was 75 percent back to normal. I was not taking medication for high blood pressure. After I had the 3rd booster vaccine, a couple of weeks, I was not feeling well and I did not know why I wasn't feeling well. I did not put the 2 things together. I was diagnosed my high blood pressure around the middle of October. The high BP results were much higher. than after the 2nd dose, 190/105. I went to see another cardiologist. He said I have high BP and he gave me BP medication. I took the BP medication and on the 3rd day I could not get out of the chair. My BP was very low. In the meantime I had all these horrible things happen. I had very high stressful situations. I went to my GP for my stress, 10/13/2021 and he prescribed Clonazepam 0.5 mg. I took a quarter of the pill on 2 occasions and then I did not take it anymore. The cardiologist said, I do not have traditional high BP. It was the mini panic attacks that were causing the high blood pressure and I should take the Clonazepam. For the last week and a half ago I took a quarter of the pill of the Clonazepam one time a day, until 2 days ago. And it kept my BP normal. My blood pressure seems returning to normal, after I take the antianxiety medication. I don't know what is going to happen, it's to new for me to understand. For the last 2 days I have not taken the anti-anxiety pill and my BP appears to be normal. I do not know if my high BP is caused from the vaccine or the high stress that is happening.

On Thursday, 11/18/21, I used the walk in service for vaccinations/immunizations. It was understood that my 8yo daughter was given the COVID Jr vaccine in the right arm and seasonal flu shot in the left arm. Today, 11/19/2021, I received a phone call from my local Pharmacy Manager,  calling to report that there was human error and that in fact my daughter DID NOT get the Covid vaccine but was given 2 flu shots. He asked about any symptoms which I explained that she reported right there after her shot in the right arm that her arm was burning. I gave my daughter Tylenol when we got home and she went straight to bed tired. She woke up this morning with sore arms and given another dose of Tylenol. Once I had received this information from pharmacist, I called Public Health, my child's school, and my daughters drs office for guidance. The school nurse took her vitals and screened her and reported that there were no other symptoms but soreness. Public Health informed me that they would be reaching out to the office to inquire if they would be completing a VARES but that either way they would do the same. At this time there have been no other symptoms but was told by pharmacist and Public Health that it can be 24-48hrs after.

Nurses assessed the patient and began initiating emergency care on the patient. At about 1654, 911 was called and Fire Department Paramedics arrived on scene at 1703. After careful assessment by both nurses and Paramedics, the patients was ruled out as not experiencing an allergic reaction. Patient's condition began to improve and he went home with his father.

This marketed literature report has been received from the authors of the published literature article as stated below, concerning a 22-year-old male patient with pre�B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia who underwent myeloablative allogeneic hematopoietic cell transplantation (HCT) from a HLA-identical unrelated donor using a peripheral blood allograft 4 years prior to presentation. His post-HCT course was complicated by acute graft-vs-host disease (GVHD) of the skin, eyes, gastrointestinal tract, and liver requiring intensified immunosuppression with tacrolimus, itacitinib, and prednisone. After clinical resolution of GVHD, all iatrogenic immunosuppression was discontinued on day +1335. Nine days post vaccination, he presented to the Hematology and Oncology Clinic with fevers up to 40�C (104�F), sore throat, nonproductive cough, and tender cervical lymphadenopathy. Twelve days post vaccination, he returned to the Hematology and Oncology Clinic after an asymptomatic, faint pink, maculopapular rash developed on his face and spread to his torso and upper extremities. He did not have conjunctivitis or coryza. He denied any recent measles exposures, sick contacts, or international travel. After consultation with Transplant Infectious Diseases, Clinical Epidemiology and Infection Prevention, and the Public Health, a diagnostic evaluation for vaccine-derived measles (Measles post vaccine) was performed. Serum measles immunoglobulin M antibody was positive and immunoglobulin G antibody was negative. Measles RNA was detected by polymerase chain reaction in urine and throat specimens. Viral genotyping by sequence analysis confirmed the strain to be genotype A (vaccine-derived) measles. He received a single dose of intravenous immunoglobulin (IVIG) 400 mg/kg. His symptoms resolved without sequelae. Despite his attendance at the Hematology and Oncology Clinic where other vulnerable individuals with solid tumor malignancies, hematologic malignancies, and HCT recipients were also present, no secondary cases occurred. The authors considered the event of vaccine-derived measles to be related to the suspect therapy. Upon internal review, the event of Measles post vaccine was considered medically significant.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Acute graft versus host disease; Allogenic stem cell transplantation (from a HLA-identical unrelated donor)

No Medical History information was reported.   On 09-Feb-2021 at 7:03 AM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 13-Mar-2021 at 7:58 AM, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 07-Nov-2021 at 4:09 AM, received third dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to .25 milliliter. On 07-Nov-2021, the patient experienced EXPIRED PRODUCT ADMINISTERED (Possible AE: doses might have been administered after 24 hour exposure to RT/Vaccine administered to 2 patients from a vial that was post temperature excursion). In November 2021, the patient experienced VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Arm soreness). On an unknown date, the patient experienced PRODUCT TEMPERATURE EXCURSION ISSUE (Possible AE: doses might have been administered after 24 hour exposure to RT/Vaccine administered to 2 patients from a vial that was post temperature excursion). In November 2021, VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Arm soreness) had resolved. At the time of the report, PRODUCT TEMPERATURE EXCURSION ISSUE (Possible AE: doses might have been administered after 24 hour exposure to RT/Vaccine administered to 2 patients from a vial that was post temperature excursion) had resolved.        For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   Concomitant medication was not reported.  Treatment medication was not reported. On 05-Nov-2021, the patient experienced BACK PAIN (lower back ache), CHILLS (really bad chills) and ARTHRALGIA (the top of her  shoulder, and the lower base of her neck became very sore and swollen.Those areas were also very tender). On an unknown date, the patient experienced PERIPHERAL SWELLING (Just like the first shot, the shot caused them to get their arm to be swollen), NECK PAIN (top of her  shoulder, and the lower base of her neck became very sore and swollen.Those areas were also very tender), VACCINATION SITE ERYTHEMA (Arm to be red), VACCINATION SITE INDURATION (Arm hard as a rock) and HEADACHE (Have a dull headache). Company Comment: This case concerns a 67 year old female with relevant medical history of Spinal cord disease , who experienced non-serious unexpected event of back pain , expected event of chills and arthralgia one day  after vaccination with the 2nd dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine ( Moderna Covid 19 vaccine ) . Two days after vaccination with the 2nd dose , she experienced non-serious unexpected event of swelling ( swollen at the top and superior to the clavicle and up into the lower part and base of the neck and top of neck ) and Tenderness . On an unknown date  patient experienced non-serious expected events of Vaccination site swelling, vaccination site erythema and vaccination site induration. The age of the patient and history of spinal disorder can be considered as a confounder for this case since elderly patient usually experiences joint pains and spinal disorders can manifest as pain. The benefit -risk relationship of mRNA-1273 Vaccine ( Moderna Covid 19 Vaccine ) is not affected by this report. A 12-years-old male patient received second dose of (BNT162B2 PFIZER BIONTECH, Solution for injection, Lot Number: FE3592; Expiration Date: 20Nov2021) Intramuscular in Left deltoid on 15Sep2021 at 09:48 for covid-19 immunisation.  The patient medical history was none. Concomitant medications were not reported. The patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (Lot Number FE3592) , Intramuscular in Left deltoid on 08Aug2021 at 16:26 as single dose. On 30Jul2021 the patient had received Vaccine Gardasil 9 (Manufacture: Merck, Batch/lot#: T028582) intramuscular in left deltoid and Vaccine Energix B (Manufacture: GSK, Batch/lot#: J7H4D) intramuscular Right deltoid previous doses 2. On 15Sep2021 the day of the patient's second dose the caller stated that the patient received all 6 doses of the pfizer-biontech covid-19 vaccine in one single dose, the vaccine was diluted and they drew up the whole vial. They normally used a 1ml syringe and instead that day the new person used a 3cc (milliliters) syringe because they were in training. This allowed a larger volume to be pulled up from the vial and caused the overdose event. A multi-dose vial of a Pfizer Vaccine was given to a child of 12 years of age all in one day. The event required visit to Emergency Room. The patient complained of fever, fatigue, headache, soreness at injection site, chills, sleepy, dizziness, right ear drainage, vomiting x 1 and decreased appetite. Temporarily treatment included Tylenol, ibuprofen and cetirizine. The patient was monitored at home for 3 days. On 22Sep2021 EKG (Electrocardiogram) showed normal result. The outcome of the events was unknown.  Amendment: This follow up is being submitted to amend previously reported information: the case is serious, the event overdose is considered serious as medical significant.  Additional information received on 21Sep2021, 06Oct2021 and 07Oct2021 from a contactable nurse  includes vaccination doses details and lot numbers, past drug vaccines history, none medical history, new events (fever, fatigue, headache, soreness at injection site, chills, sleepy, dizziness, right ear drainage, vomiting x 1 and decreased appetite), treatment and EKG result.   No follow-up attempts are needed. No further information is expected.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information provided, a contributory role of the suspect product BNT162B2 to the reported events cannot be excluded in the setting of accidental overdose. It was noted that patient received all 6 doses of the pfizer-biontech covid-19 vaccine in one single dose. Case will be reassessed upon receipt of additional information. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

Husband states the patient has been recently discharged home from the hospital and was placed in rehab for treatment.  States he saw her couple days ago and she was eating and was able to carry on a conversation.  States he was called today and told she was short of breath.  He states she appears more weak and is coughing more than she had been.  Patient does have a previous diagnosis of Covid.
LAB_DATA: This patient is brought to the emergency department with complaint of cough, shortness of breath, and hypoxia.  On exam patient has diminished lung sounds and dry mucous membranes.  ABG reveals hypoxia with a PaO2 of 70.5 on 100% nonrebreather.  Patient's pH is 7.456, PCO2 is 23.1.  IV access established labs are drawn.  Patient is given a 1 L fluid bolus.  IV access established baseline labs are drawn.  Patient is placed on BiPAP for respiratory support secondary to hypoxia.  Patient is a DO NOT RESUSCITATE with no intubation.  Patient's Covid swab is positive.  Patient's blood work does reveal a slightly elevated white blood cell count of 14.8, hyponatremia with a sodium of 158 and hypokalemia with potassium of 3.3.  Patient has acute renal failure with a BUN of 9 0 and a creatinine of 3.7, in January 2021 patient's renal function was normal.  Urinalysis is 4+ bacteria.  Chest x-ray does show streaky infiltrate or atelectasis in the right and left lower lung base as well as the lingula.  Patient is started on Rocephin.  Case is discussed with on-call hospitalist Dr. who accepts the admission.  Patient is given 10 mEq potassium in the emergency department.

9/24 - got first dose of pfizer. 15 min or so after getting shot, didn?t feel right.  Head felt strange, faint, chest tightness/pressure, palpitations, throat felt swollen, weakness/pain/tingling down left arm, left hand aching, panicky feeling.  Severe symptoms lasted about an hour; chest tightness/aching and left arm/hand issues subdued but never went away.    That weekend - bouts of the same episode above after putting anything in my body.  Coffee, ibuprofen, eating food.  Chest tightness/pressure and left arm/hand issues continued ongoing.  Palpitations and panicky feeling come and go.  Rash/sores on my face; cold sore on my lip.  Extremity weakness, dizziness, periods of fatigue and then surging energy (like waking up at night with enough energy to clean the whole house).  Left hand and eye begin twitching.  Overall, just feeling awful and knowing something isn?t right.  Seem sensitive to everything; can?t eat or do things as normal.  Stopped drinking coffee or taking any medication.  9/27 - call w/dr.  Prescribed vistiril and xanax.    Took Vistaril the next 5 days.  Helped in that it made me groggy and could just go to sleep.  Skin rash/sores begin to immediately clear up.  Once med would wear off, all the same issues above come back.  Left hand/eye twitching getting worse.  10/1 - mentally slow processing/foggy, hyper-sensitive to noise and motion, difficulty conversing with people/understanding what they?re saying, hallucinations (seeing shadows), felt like I was going out of my mind, woke up that night with severe cramping/spasms in left hand, spasms in forehead/eyes/right side of face, couldn?t feel left side of face, same heart issues.  Sharp pains in back of head.  Stopped taking vistaril  10/2 - struggled through day with heart issues and body spasms; left hand/eye pretty constant, but differ in severity.  Woke up again at night with spasms/head pressure/ pain  10/3 - called to see about going to hospital; went to urgent care.  Dr. wants all this reported to vaccine registry; thinks having an autoimmune reaction. Didn?t think Guillain Barre at this point.  Echo scheduled for 10/19  The next week - same issues waxing and waning.  Heart issues much more subdued.  Spasms migrated to right side of body (last about 10-15 min in other areas); feet/hands/arms/eyes, but most severe on left side.  The above issues waxed and waned for a solid month after getting vaccine before really starting to subdue.  To date, still having issues with sensitivities (can't tolerate weak coffee or alcohol, certain foods), fatigue/weakness, occasional spasms/tremors, chest pain/tightness.  Symptoms seem to relapse if do too much of normal routine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My initial symptoms were the somewhat typical adverse effects, fatigue, headache/pain up the back of my neck, brainfog which I attributed to the fatigue.  I also developed a 10 day frontal headache with intermittent migraines headaches.  I have had migraines in the past, but not for years.  All of these eventually went away.  The symptoms that are still bothering me are that I still feel like I have  brain fog and my essential tremors got significantly worse.   I noticed that within a week after getting the first vaccine.  They may have been worse sooner, but with the headaches and fatigue I hadn't noticed them.
LAB_DATA: I saw my provider for my annual physical on October 21.  There were no tests done at that time related to the adverse effects.  She offered to put my on some medicine, but I refused in hopes that the tremors would improve, but they have not.  I think I told her my tremors worsened after the 2nd shot, but when I went back and looked at my calendar, I realized it was after the first one.  My father-in-law passed away and it first became obvious to me how bad they were at his funeral which was September 23rd.  They have gotten even worse since then, after the second shot.  I did not discuss the brain fog with her.  I had mentioned the headaches to her prior via messaging.
OTHER_MEDS: I believe I quit taking everything, but I am not positive.  If not, I could have been taking Vitamin C, a multivitamin, Biotin, Calcium, and Glucosomine/Chondroitin

[I'm reporting a "breakthrough" COVID-19 infection with this form after speaking with a CDC representative on the phone about my latest V-Safe submission. I'm also describing some post-acute symptoms I've experienced. To be clear, I do not associate any of these symptoms with my vaccination itself.]  On September 21, I received a positive test result for COVID-19. I was experiencing a fever, loss of smell, cough, and congestion, which prompted me to get tested. During my isolation period I treated symptoms with DayQuil and ibuprofen. On the 25th, most symptoms were resolved, but I experienced some slightly difficult breathing (not wheezing, but the feeling of "incomplete" breaths) and chest/intercostal muscle tightness. This was accompanied by notable feelings of anxiety/worry. I was examined by EMTs at my home, who noted normal blood oxygen levels and blood pressure. They advised my breathing seemed within norms, and not the "shortness of breath" that would indicate a severe problem (since I was able to speak without interruption). On the 27th I spoke with a provider at my PCP's office, who agreed that I was not at high risk, but prescribed an albuterol inhaler to be used as needed. This appeared to help, although the mental/emotional symptoms were still somewhat present.  Around October 30/31 I started to notice similar muscle tightness and "incomplete" breaths, provoking a significant anxiety response again. I did my best to self-manage with the albuterol, muscle stretching, and meditation. On November 1 I was seen by an urgent care center, with a follow-up chest x-ray on November 3. The x-ray was described to me as "normal, with some bronchitis" and I was advised to continue using the albuterol. I spoke with my PCP, on November 8, who recommended I switch from the albuterol to Flovent (fluticasone) since albuterol can increase heart rate and perceived anxiety. I've been on that course since November 13, and the symptoms seem to be well-managed so far.
LAB_DATA: 21 September 2021: positive result for COVID-19 (Qualitative NAAT) 3 November 2021: CBC (all results normal), chest X-ray (detailed results not available to me)  I didn't see another place to provide this information: my first vaccination dose was on 04/29/2021 and my second was on 05/19/2021
OTHER_MEDS: Daily: Truvada (emtricitabine-tenofovir (TDF) 200-300 mg), valacyclovir (500 mg), vitamin D supplement

Patient was given vaccine, and in 5 minutes she walked up to the counter and stated that she felt as if her tongue was tingling.  At that time, my technician spoke to her and reported the event to me.  She was able to swallow and when I looked at her tongue and throat, there was no swelling present.  Patient was given diphenhydramine 50 mg at that time, and I sat her in a chair that had arms on it.  I proceeded to put a pulse ox on her.  Her O2 sat was 98 percent and heart rate was 73.  The pulse ox was left on throughout the entire time that I was with the patient.   Patient started saying that she was feeling tired, proceeded by nausea.  In about 3 more minutes, the patient stated that she was feeling like she was going to pass out.  I asked if she could lie down in the floor so that she would not hit her head if she passed out.  While getting the patient from the chair to the floor, patient stated that her legs were heavy.  I assisted her to the floor, and her legs were shaky and wobbly.  While assisting her to the floor, I had to physically hold the patient up.   I had ice packs on her neck, which she stated that were helping her to feel better.   She then stated that she felt as if her throat was tingling and that her lips and tongue were feeling worse.  At this time, I asked an employee to call 911, as the patient was feeling worse.  Medical personnel were here, and within minutes were assessing the patient.  The patient was taken via ambulance to Medical Center.   At around 3:30 PM, patient called and said the hospital had released her home, and she was told to continue taking diphenhydramine 25 mg TID for 24 hours.
OTHER_MEDS: Patient does not fill medication at this pharmacy.
CUR_ILL: Patient did not report any illness to me at the time of vaccination.
HISTORY: Patient does not fill at this pharmacy, and no long term health conditions were reported except diabetes.
ALLERGIES: Patient does not fill at this pharmacy, and did not list allergies.  The allergies were given to the emergency personnel.

I went to my doctor to just make sure that it wasn't something like my blood pressure being off, but that was fine. She checked my blood sugar and that was the best it had been in years. I also got my thyroid levels checked and they were fine too. I told her that at that point, I wasn't sleeping as much, but it worried me that I was sleeping a lot. Patient received her Moderna vaccine booster on 11/5/21. Reports last colonoscopy ~ 10 yrs ago that was reportedly normal.  CT abd was done on admission that showed Marked mural edema involving the transverse colon, with relative sparing of the distal transverse colon and splenic flexure region. Findings are consistent with colitis and could be related to infectious or inflammatory colitis. Ischemic colitis should also be considered.  She was seen by GI, general surgery and oncology, appropriate w/up was done - not felt  related to cancer immunotherapy nor infection.  CT abd mesenteric protocol was done 11/15/21: 1.  Persistent mural edema involving a long segment of the mid transverse colon, slightly improved in the interval. There is induration of the paracolic fat. There appears to be enhancement of the edematous bowel wall; however, the enhancement does appear relatively diminished; although difficult to assess due to the still fairly pronounced bowel wall edema. No vascular occlusion is identified. Ischemia due to low flow states cannot be excluded on the basis of this exam and may be intermittent; therefore, clinical correlation is recommended.  Pt's BCx remain negative and has intermittent low grade fevers,  had firm BMs (no diarrhea), was covered with antibiotics but etiology of her transverse colitis remained unclear and thought to be vaccine related.

Dr. cleared me to receive my second dosage of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination.  After receiving my second vaccination I experience a headache, mild fever, fatigue, confusion within a one-hour time frame. The soreness, swelling, and warmth to the touch at the injection site followed hours later. I was bed resting for two days before the symptoms subsided. On November 7, 2021, walking from my bedroom to the kitchen I started experiencing shooting pain from my waist down my leg on my left side enabling me from walking. I had to rely on my daughter and fianc�? to assist me with laying down, walking, and using the restroom. My muscles on my left side became weak and begin to have spam. On November 8, 2021, I made an appointment with my healthcare provider Dr. On November 9, 2021, I followed up with Dr. concerning the pain I was experiencing. Dr. prescribe me Acetaminophen/Codeine 300-30mg TAB and Cyclobenzaprine HY 10mg TAB.  The medication Dr. prescribed was not effective. I continue to have pain in my left side. On November 16, 2021, I started experiencing pain in my chest and back. November 17, 2021, I went to  Urgent Care for treatment. Dr. , diagnosed me with possible sciatica. Dr. , prescribe Methocarbamol 750mg TAB and heat therapy on the affected area 4 times a day. Dr. , advise me to follow up with my healthcare provider. Dr. , also request that I be on bed rest from November 17, 2021, and return to work on November 21, 2021. The medication that Dr., prescribed allowed me to be mobile again but the pain still exists. Dr. referred me to radiology for an x-ray of the back.  It?s going on three weeks since I received the second Pfizer COVID vaccination lot number FF8841. The pain on my left side has continued to be a problem since the third day of receiving the Pfizer COVID vaccination lot number FF8841. I have been suffering pain, spasms, weakness on my left side, chest, and back pain. I have trouble walking, sitting, laying, and getting up from a sitting position due to the pain. I also missed work due to my complications after receiving the COVID-19 vaccination.

Patient went unconscious immediately and PHN began to hear a gurgling noise, PHN took off his face mask, checked his airway nothing was found, rolled him onto his right side, PHN helped and lifted his legs. Patient was out for about 15 seconds. PHN then placed him back onto his back and he began to talk. He then went out again and made the gurgling noise, his face turned red. PHN assessed airway, nothing found rolled patient onto his right side. PHN continued to hold his legs up, he was out for approximately 15 seconds again. Patient returned to conscious level and was placed back onto his back, he began talking to the nurses and stated he has a history of vasovagal episodes, patient was encouraged to take a few deep breaths. PHN asked if he had eaten before coming in today, he stated he had not. He was given a cookie and a juice, he had two sips of the juice. The ambulance was called at 8:30am by site lead. PHN notified patient that the ambulance was on the way, vital signs were taken B/P 120/70, P86, O2 Sat 99% RA, he remained lying on the floor until the ambulance arrived at 8:50m. He continued to have trouble with orthostatic hypotension, the ambulance crew took him to the hospital.
LAB_DATA: 911 was called and he was transported to the hospital
PRIOR_VAX: patient reported this after both vaccines had been administered that this has happened to him 5-6 times prior

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my Moderna booster shoot Friday afternoon and woke up a 4 AM on Saturday with a fast heart rate. It was so fast that I thought I could die and I called 911. I was breathing fairly normally and able to walk around and converse. Upon arrival of the paramedics, I had my vitals checked. My pulse rate felt quite a bit lower when checked than when I called 911 but it was still 155 BPM and very steady when breathing in and out and trying to calm down. The paramedics said my blood pressure was high and left it up to me whether I wanted to be admitted. I decided against given that my family had gotten back to me and were on their way. I took my temperature and it was 100.2. I took ibuprofen and my pulse rate and fever slowly went down. I had the Jansen vaccine in early April and experienced similar symptoms, but not as dramatically or serious, so I didn't report or call 911 then.
LAB_DATA: Heart rate, blood pressure, temperature taken.
PRIOR_VAX: Similar but less dramatic and severe symptoms from my initial Jansen vaccination in April 2021.

After the first dose, it hit me at 3pm with flu like symptoms and sore arm. That remained through the weekend. It had somewhat subsided prior to my second dose. However after the second dose again I had flu like symptoms. but all my symptoms increased and became worse. I had increased migraines, dizzy spells, diarrhea, excruciating pain, numbness on the right side of my face, sensitivity to noise, increased vertigo, ringing in my ears, nausea, rash, shortness of breath, sensitivity to light and smells along with brain fog. I have lost 15 pounds over the last 7 months. At times I have shooting pain up either side of my neck into my eye. Bright lights cause flare ups of these symptoms. All of this I have had EVERY SINGLE DAY FOR THE LAST 7 MONTHS.  Following the second shot, I went back to my doctor around April 26th because I had become so sensitive to noise along with ringing in my ears and wanted to get my hearing checked. I was refer for PT as my balance was really affected. I had weekly visits between May and August  There were times they would touch my neck that would cause me to go into an excruciating flare-up. On June 22, 2021 I went to the ER because I was in excruciating pain. I had multiple blood test done which were unremarkable, as well as a UA.  I went again on July 8th, 2021 and they diagnosed me with vertigo and wanted to give me valium, which I declined. In July I went to a hearing and balance specialist, and was told that the vaccine had caused my  immune system to go into overdrive and attack the vestibular of my right ear at 33% . Overall impressions was unilateral weakness of 33% indicative of right peripheral deficit. A hearing test on 10/29/21 noted slight hearing loss in my right ear. In August I was referred  to an upper cervical chiropractor who I am still seeing with 3 visits remaining. I also was place on a heart monitor for 3 days - those results are not in my chart at this time.
LAB_DATA: blood work negative  April 27, 21 MRI inner auditory canal, 1.4 cm signal abnormality in L parietal white matter,  June 22, 21 Head CT  - negative July 22, 21  MRA /Brain with MRI angiogram neck w/ wo contrast, negative

A day after the second shot I got a fever of 101.3 that lasted two more days.  My lymph nodes on my left side under my arm and my neck were swollen.  The ones under the arm hurt.  I knew swelling of nodes was common so I waited for them to go down.  They did not, and the one on the left side of my neck got bigger.  After 3 months I went to my doctor's PA and she was concerned that my nodes were so large.  She ordered several tests, I was cleared for breast cancer after several diagnostic tests.  but when I went to an ENT specialist he had me get a sonogram of the neck.  The node was larger than a quarter (25 cent piece) and since it was so large and had been there for so long, he recommended having it surgically removed., which I did.  The pathology reported the results were consistent with reactive changes, and not diagnostic for malignancy.   Basically, this very stressful and terrifying situation was all due to the vaccine.  I wish I never got it.  I should have relied on my own very good immune system
LAB_DATA: Surgery to remove the lymph node, sonogram, mammogram, cbc

On Oct. 25, I had a sore throat. Over the next few days, I developed a cough and lots of sinus drainage. Soon, the sinus drainage became mainly congestion with an occasional cough. Within a week or a week and a half, it started to feel like I was getting a sinus infection (cough and pain in my upper molars). On Oct. 30, I went to an immediate care facility and got a rapid COVID test, which came back negative. A few days later, I went on a strong, 12-hour decongestant (generic of Claritin), which helped a bit but not much. After being sick for two and a half weeks, I went to the doctor, on Nov. 11.  He informed me that this kind of ongoing sinus congestion has commonly been seen in those with the COVID vaccine that came down with COVID, but he did not say for sure that this was my case. Since I was past the two week point of sickness, he didn't feel it was necessary to test me for COVID, so I chose not to be tested that day. He prescribed an antibiotic, which has helped my congestion and illness go away.

The medical assistant at the site was vaccinating patients. The clinic was held by HR support at  High School at 1. Rocket. The clinician had drawn up 3 vaccinations for those waiting. 2 Moderna boosters and 1 Pfizer booster. All boosters were labelled with the color coded sticker for that vaccine and had the name of the vaccine on each sticker and had the designated card for each patient in the tray. The MA took the next patients tray with her vaccine card and Modrena booster. When the MA called the patient, she stated she wanted another person to go ahead of her because she had an appointment and was in a  rush. This patient wanted the Pfizer booster and the MA did not replace the previous patients tray and grab the correct one. As a result, the MA went through vaccine verification and vaccine history and administered the vaccine without realizing she has the wrong vaccine. Once realized, the MA apologized to the patient, the clinician explained the boosters can be interchangeable but of course the patient was a little upset. The patients card was corrected. Management notified of incident, safety officers and LNO's notified of incident. No adverse events noted post vaccine.

BP 134/83 and HR 65 on over-the-counter BP monitor on-site. No cardiac history. History of anxiety w/ and w/o panic attacks, but patient reports this is well-controlled and today's symptoms are not consistent with this history. Patient does not want ambulance called, but staff explained that our medical obligation is to call 911 for life-threatening symptoms such as chest pain/tightness/pressure/heaviness. 1605 - Provider on-site called 911. 1615 - Ambulance arrived. HR with SR 60, BP 133/84, and SpO2 99% on their monitor, but EKG print-out has "concerning areas" that warrant evaluation by a hospital given its unclear if they were pre-existing or new and further evaluation is outside ambulance scope. Patient declined transport to a hospital, however, due to financial concerns after having lost his medical insurance when he turned 26 last month. Patient said "I'd rather die than face those medical bills" and "I truly don't care if I die".  1625 - Ambulance and on-site vaccine staff all repeated hospital transfer recommendation. Patient declined again. Ambulance left. 1635 - Given resources for, Marketplace, and several Portland-area low-income, sliding scale medical offices. Additionally recommended messaging his PCP to discuss whether 2nd Pfizer dose is advised, because messaging can still occur at no cost without health insurance. 1645 - Patient escorted to car by staff for continued observation. No change to 5/10 "chest heaviness". Otherwise stable. Patient left in vehicle.
PRIOR_VAX: Hospitalization after TDaP as a child. Specifics unknown.

On March 27 2021 I got my second covid shot.  Around April 5th I noticed a weird feeling of pressure in my chest.  I had a yearly physical already scheduled for April 9 so I alerted my doctor in advance that I was feeling some chest pressure and fluttering.  On April 9 he did an EKG as part of my physical and did not seem concerned but said to wait a while and see what happens but if I felt faint or chest pains to go to hospital. Sounded reasonable. We did not get a heart image so I have no certainty of anything wrong with my heart. The pressure continued and then I starting having noticeable palpitations later in April and thru June.  They would last minutes.  The palpitations became worse to where my heart felt like it was pounding through my chest and I let my doctor know that I was still feeling them early June.  Still we waited, and around July I noticed that they were not as severe any more and about middle of July I noticed I did not have chest pressure or palpitations anymore.  I bring this up and report it because I am considering the booster and I wonder if the booster will finish off the attack that the second shot may have started in April and kill me this time.  It is a real concern to me and I want it known so if I get the booster and get heart issues and die that this was duly noted to the CDC and my doctor.
LAB_DATA: None we waited until symptoms went away after 3 months
